title: czech hot rolls
directions: Dissolve
teaspoons
sugar and yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Combine egg, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, butter and warm milk
in large mixing bowl.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour.
Cool flour mixture
to lukewarm,
then add yeast mixture.
Gradually add remaining flour until all ingredients are well blended.
Knead for
minutes. Cover
with
a
damp
cloth and let rise in greased
bowl
until double.
Cut dough with a tablespoon for each
roll and form in desired shape.
Place on a well-greased cookie
sheet.
Brush tops
with
butter.
Cover and let rise until double in size. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and Miracle Whip.
Sift soda with flour and add alternately with warm water.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce drop donuts
directions: Combine liquid and dry ingredients (except oil for frying and sugar-cinnamon mixture).
Drop by teaspoons into hot (365°) fat. Fry to golden brown, turning once.
Roll donuts in sugar and cinnamon.
Best when served warm.

title: marinated spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain spaghetti.
Marinate overnight in Accent, seasoned salt, lemon juice and oil.
Next day, add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: vanilla wafer cheese cakes
directions: Mix confectioners icing and spread on vanilla wafers.
Spread with pie filling and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zesty broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Combine soup, cheese, egg, milk, mayonnaise and horseradish.
Stir into broccoli and spoon into a casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and butter. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and salt.
Cook until clear.
Add jello; dissolve and cool.
Pour over berries; pour all into crust.
I use Push Pie Crust.

title: cheesy green bean casserole
directions: Combine beaten eggs with cheeses and spices.
Add bread crumbs. Put 1/2 beans in greased casserole.
Top with cheese mixture. Repeat.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water, add 2 tablespoons sugar; put into large bowl, combine buttermilk, yeast water, oil and 1 tablespoon sugar; stir well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Let dough rest 10 minutes.
Turn onto floured board and knead. Roll out and cut into rolls.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in hot oil about 15 minutes. Add shrimp, salt and cayenne. Cook, stirring until shrimp are pink (about 3 minutes).
Sprinkle the flour over the shrimp and toss to coat. Add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.

If more gravy is required, add another tablespoon flour and an additional 1/2 cup water. Stir in Tabasco sauce to taste (3 or 4 shakes is nice; more if you like it hot). If desired, sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with rice or orzo.
When serving this, make sure everything is done in advance as this cooks very quickly.

title: bethany's gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses and egg.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Shape by tablespoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen. Easily doubled.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix gently.
Serve on lettuce leaf with garnish of other fruit, i.e. cantaloupe, strawberries, etc.
Or serve in 1/2 of cantaloupe in bed of lettuce.
Use your imagination.

title: easy cheese soup
directions: Heat until all cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and half of onions, in large rectangle casserole; line bottom with tortillas which have been torn in pieces.
Cover with cooked hamburger.
Then put a layer of chili, onions and cheese.
Next layer a layer of tortillas.
Slice tamales in half lengthwise and layer with Mexican beans, green chilies, onions and more cheese.
Top with Spanish rice and more cheese.
Cover with foil but crimp it so it doesn't stick to the cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and add to potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and mix with corn flakes.
Spread over top of potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onion and place in cold water and cover for 30 minutes. Sift flour, salt and baking powder into medium bowl.
Set aside. Beat egg yolk slightly in bowl.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
Beat egg white until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Dip onion slices into batter and fry.

title: sweet dough pie crust
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, and eggs at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to egg and margarine mixture alternating with milk.
You will have to use your hands at the end to get all the flour worked in.
This will make a soft dough which must be worked into the pie pan by hand.
It cannot be rolled with a rolling pin.
Sprinkle with extra flour as you work it into the pie pan.
Reserve a small piece for the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes. (Makes enough for 3 crusts.)

title: tuna
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Sift in the flour. Blend dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls and roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: walnut cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and bake at 325° until done.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Put thawed orange juice, crushed pineapple, sugar and water in a large bowl; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cut up apricots and sliced bananas.
Freeze in foil baking cups.
Makes about 32 (1/4-cup) servings.

title: grits pilaf
directions: Stir grits, garlic and pepper into boiling chicken broth. Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until thick, 3 to 4 minutes.
Discard garlic clove (if used).
Stir in green onions and butter.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken-rice
directions: Mix all, but chicken and rice.
Place rice in casserole.
Pour mix over rice (save 1 cup).
Place chicken on top and extra mix on top of chicken.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snickers piegroves, texas
directions: Melt candy bars, peanut butter and half and half.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust. Freeze 4 to 6 hours.

title: tony's teriyaki sauce
directions: In glass dish or glass cake pan, arrange your choice of meat. Mix all above ingredients and ladle the sauce (uncooked) over top. Let set overnight in the refrigerator, then cook. Serve with vegetables or rice.

title: apricot-glazed carrots
directions: Cook scraped and cut carrots in salted water until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter and stir in preserves until blended.
Add nutmeg, salt, orange peel and lemon juice.
Toss carrots with apricot mixture until well coated. Garnish with parsley and serve at once.

title: teriyaki round
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over meat placing in deep pan 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.
Turn occasionally.
Broil or grill 45 to 55 minutes for rare, longer for well.
Baste frequently with marinade.
Keep 6 inches from heat.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Simmer chicken in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter until golden brown, adding 1/4 cup water when needed.
Cook until tender, about 45 minutes, with a tight lid on the pan.

title: easy no frost chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until well mixed. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle sugar and chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy sweet coleslaw
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: queen pudding
directions: Pour scalded milk over bread crumbs.
Add melted butter and allow to stand 15 minutes.
Beat yolks slightly and add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend well and add to bread mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Turn into greased baking dish and bake in slow oven at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until custard is firm.
Remove from oven; cool.
Spread top of pudding with the following meringue and return to oven.
Cook as directed and serve warm.

title: caramel breakfast rolls
directions: Cut 1 loaf of bread into small pieces; place pieces in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, pudding mix and milk; mix well.
Drizzle half of brown sugar mix over the dough pieces and sprinkle with half nuts and raisins.
Cut remaining dough into small pieces; place over first layer. Drizzle remaining brown sugar mix, nuts and raisins.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Early next morning, bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts; reserve broth. When chicken is cool, shred very finely and place in mixing bowl. Add the can of chicken broth to reserved broth. Break vermicelli into 3 parts and add to broth along with the chopped onion. To the chicken, add the chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, corn, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Mix well. When vermicelli is done, drain and add to the chicken mixture. Add cubed Velveeta cheese and mix well. Transfer to a 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add fruit cocktail, egg and 1/2 ??? butter.
Mix 1/2 minute by hand.
Cover with a mixture of 1 cup brown sugar, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350°.

title: lazy pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour mixture on top of meringue. Pour in pie filling.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix; do not stir.
Makes its own crust.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press into pie plate, reserving some for sprinkling on top.
Beat egg yolks; add to milk.
Stir into cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook until mixture coats spoon, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into pie shell.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cut apples
into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients. Better if
refrigerated overnight before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pickled beets or relish
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil vinegar, brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Pour over beets.
Let stand at least 8 hours.
This keeps well in a covered jar or dish in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill well.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberries (do not drain).
Let set in refrigerator until thick. Fold in whipped topping and nuts.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix butter, oil, sugar and eggs; add vanilla and sour milk. Then add spices, salt, flour and then cocoa.
Then add grated zucchini.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, then sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over cake before baking.
Bake 45 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, eggs, 3/4 stick melted butter, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased casserole dish.
Remove and top with cornflakes, brown sugar, pecans and 3/4 stick butter.
Bake another 10 minutes at 400°.

title: oven baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil about 5 minutes on each side in ovenproof skillet.
Mix together soup, milk, Lea & Perrins, celery salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Arrange onion slices over chops.
Pour soup mix over all.
Add mushrooms.
Cover with foil.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and chill.
When ready to serve, add remaining ingredients.
Combine all well, then serve. Yield:
6 servings.

title: ham-broccoli rolls
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and let cool. Set aside.
Between 2 sheets of waxed paper (or on a lightly floured board), roll out each biscuit to a 7 1/2 or 8-inch oval. On each biscuit, spread a thin layer of prepared mustard (about 1 teaspoon).
Place a layer of chunk ham that has been flaked with a fork and then a layer of the cooked, cooled broccoli.
Roll jellyroll style, beginning at the smaller end, overlap edges and pinch together to seal.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 25 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered confectioners sugar on top.

title: candy bar fudge
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the butter, cocoa, brown sugar and milk. Microwave on High until mixture boils, about 3 minutes. Stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla. Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan. In another microwave-safe bowl, heat caramels and water on High for 2 minutes or until melted. Stir in peanuts; spread over chocolate layer. Microwave chocolate chips on High for 1 minute or until melted; spread over caramel layer. Chill until firm. Yields 2 3/4 pounds.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Wilt onion in bacon or butter. Add paprika, chicken and salt to taste; brown.
Add water; cover and simmer until tender.
Remove chicken from pan.
Mix sour cream with flour; stir carefully into pan.
Simmer gravy for 5 minutes. Strain over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: mother's red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add beaten eggs, food coloring and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt, add with buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar; fold into batter.
Bake in 3 floured and greased layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch pans.
Cream sugar, Crisco and Wesson oil.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, flour and coconut.
Add egg yolks; beat in 1 at a time.
Fold in stiffly-beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Toss together the potatoes, salt and celery seed.
Remove yolks from eggs.
Dice egg whites and add to potato mixture. Blend cucumber, onion, mustard, salad dressing, vinegar and egg yolks in electric blender.
Fold sour cream into this mixture and fold this dressing into potatoes.
Chill well.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Slices of ham arranged around salad make it very pretty.

title: pecan delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix together the flour, soft margarine and chopped pecans until crumbly.
Press in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together.
Let marinate for several hours.
Serve with vegetables.
Can be used with chips but vegetables are better.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix above ingredients together and pour into greased and floured 11x17 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with margarine, eggs, water, walnuts and chocolate bits.
Grease a pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brownies
directions: Beat butter and sugar to a cream.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, cocoa, nuts and salt.
Put in spoonfuls on oven tray and bake 15 minutes at 180°C.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix all, except coconut, well.
Fold in coconut and pour mixture into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese treat
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam) with 1 package crescent rolls.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and egg yolk. Spread mixture over crescent lined pan.
Spread other package crescent rolls over mixture.
Pinch to seal seams.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Spoon over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle mixture of cinnamon, sugar and nuts over egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: blueburgs
directions: Divide meat into eight portions.
Flatten each portion into a thin patty.
In a small bowl, combine cheeses with a fork until well blended.
Add garlic and onion, mixing well.
Divide the cheese mixture between four patties, topping with the remaining patties.
Seal each patty.
Place on a platter and put in the freezer about 1/2 hour before grilling to seal patties well. Grill over hot charcoal until well browned.
Serves 4.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist; do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes.
Cool and peel.
Grate coarse. Combine first 6 ingredients and mix.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Smooth top.

title: green party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice together.
Chill for several hours or freeze to a slush.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: hawaiian turkey balls
directions: Combine turkey, onion, green pepper and salt; mix well.
Shape into 24 balls.
Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Brown turkey balls over medium heat.
Drain any fat.
Add soup, water, pineapple, soy sauce and ginger.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.

title: homemade danish dessert
directions: Make Kool-Aid with 7 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and clear jell
and remaining water.
Stir into Kool-Aid and cook until thickened.
Remove
from
heat
and
add jello. Chill; add strawberries, if desired.
Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: plump molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Add molasses and lemon juice; blend well.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add boiling water.
Mix well; chill thoroughly. Set oven at 350°.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet (4 dozen cookies).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in green beans, tomato soup, water, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare instant mashed potatoes (enough for 4 servings) according to directions, except omit milk.
Add one beaten egg; stir in a little milk if necessary to make potatoes fluffy, yet stiff enough to hold their shape.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drop potatoes in mounds on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: simple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir in raisins.
Place bread, buttered sides up, in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Pour milk mixture over bread. Pour boiling water in a pan, larger than the 9-inch dish and place in the oven.
Put baking dish in the larger pan, making sure the boiling water comes halfway up the side of the baking dish.

title: salmon dip
directions: Place drained salmon on a plate. Clean off all skin and dark spots on salmon. Break into small pieces. In a bowl, beat cream cheese with milk until smooth. Add mayonnaise and liquid smoke and beat again until smooth. Add salmon and beat until well blended. Place in container and store in refrigerator to season. Use with chips or crackers.

title: mess sergeant french dressing
directions: Combine all the above ingredients, either in a small jar and shake well, or blend for a few seconds in blender.
Keep refrigerated.
Shake before using.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together refried beans and the taco seasoning mix.
Then mix together the black olives, green chiles, chopped pimentos and the Ortego chiles.
Mix together the avocados and the sour cream. Now add all these in layers, top with chopped tomatoes and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: sweet sydney's cereal puffs
directions: Beat egg whites to a foam.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold in cereal.
Drop 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 14 minutes or until brown at 325°.
Cool.
Enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Tear in small pieces.
In casserole dish, layer chicken and stuffing mix.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake.

title: asparagus-and-english peas
directions: Cook asparagus according to directions.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish, greased.
Cook peas and drain.
Layer peas, mushrooms and pimiento.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter. Add flour and cook 1 minute.
Combine asparagus liquid and milk. Add flour mixture. Cook on low heat until thickened.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables in casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons melted butter. Sprinkle over sauce.
Can refrigerate overnight. Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix beans together; put in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle hamburger on top of beans.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on hamburger.
Pour mild taco sauce on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with black and green olives.
Serve with Mexican rice or chips.
Teenage children love this casserole.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg with applesauce, vanilla, and vegetable oil. Add remaining ingredients except blueberries and stir to blend. Gently fold in blueberries. Drop in paperlined muffin cups. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crushed onion rings, cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings in a plastic bag. Beat egg and milk.
Dip chicken in egg and milk; shake in onion and cheese mixture.
Place in 11 x 9-inch pan.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 5.

title: janice's egg casserole
directions: Put bread in large casserole dish.
Combine milk and eggs. Add cheese and green chilies.
Pour over bread.
Add salt. Refrigerate overnight.
Set out one hour before cooking, then bake one hour at 350° or 45 minutes at 375°.

title: saucy beef and rice
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Serve over bed of fluffy rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind orange (peeling and all), pineapple, cranberries and sugar.
Put in jello, dissolved over hot water.
Add nuts and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf or otherwise.

title: "whitaker and hall ole pork chop quikie"(according to the size of your family.)
directions: Take your pork chops and lay them in a deep pan.
Salt and pepper the meat, then chop up your onion.
Spread them out over top, making sure it's all covered.
Cook in oven at 450°, until pork chops are beginning to brown.
Remove from oven (be careful .. "hot") and pour pork and beans on top of meat.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of all that.
Put back in oven for another 30 minutes or so.
Serve with a green salad, some corn-on-the-cob and homemade biscuits.
M. M. Good!

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together and form into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix together; beat 10 minutes.
Pour into 3 medium tins (greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken herbed fricassee
directions: Buy chicken cut up.
Arrange in shallow pan.
Brush with some of the salad oil.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour and milk, to the salad oil; pour over chicken.
Bake about 20 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix bread with milk, sugar and butter.
Pour over eggs.
Add vanilla and raisins; mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: coconut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs, one at a time.
Mix ingredients as listed.
Cook for 15 minutes in a 450° oven, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: everyday rolls
directions: Scald milk. Add sugar, salt and shortening. Cool until lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water and stir.
Put a little sugar in yeast water to dissolve. Combine milk mixture and 1 cup flour. Stir by hand.
Add yeast and egg.
Stir in remaining flour, a little at a time; beat after each addition until you have a soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place, 1 to 1 1/2 hours until double.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Toss and coat with flour; knead about 15 times.
Make balls.
Coat with butter.
Let rise in pan 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain and mash through a dicer.
In a large bowl, add to potatoes the melted butter, sugar and condensed milk.
Mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs; mix well. Pour into ready prepared pie crust, uncooked.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° or until done.
Yields 3 pies.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cut up tomatoes,
onions,
hot peppers and bell pepper. Add vinegar and sugar.	Cook until thick.
Makes 3 pints.

title: citrus punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add to instant tea.
Add juices; chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ice cubes and stir until ice is partially melted.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish with lime slices and maraschino cherries.
Yield:
44 servings.

title: amaretto chantilly
directions: Combine miniature marshmallows and Amaretto in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Cook until marshmallows melt, stirring occasionally.
Stir in lemon juice, almond extract and cherries.
Cool slightly.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into marshmallow mixture.
Spoon
into individual serving dishes.
Cover and freeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vanilla crumb cake
directions: Mix together vanilla wafers, pecans and coconut.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix with dry ingredients and cook in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: mexican baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 3 or 4 hours.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations. Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread onto tortillas.
Roll up and slice into bite size pieces.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars and egg.
Add flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mid american chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, vegetables, soup mix and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
In large Dutch oven, melt butter; stir in flour and mix until smooth. Slowly add milk and cook over low heat until thickened; stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in corn and cooked vegetables.
Heat (not boil).
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Bake the cake at 350° until brown.
Blend pudding and milk together.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread this on cake. Top with cherries and coconut.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not overlay chicken. Use additional pan, if necessary.
Shake bottle of dressing before pouring.
After shaking dressing bottle, pour over chicken.
Bake chicken at 350° in oven for about 1
hour.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Blend in peanut butter.
Put corn flakes in well-greased bowl and pour hot mixture over corn flakes.
Shape into balls.
Yield: 100 balls.

title: todd's best chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken, then cut into small chunks.
Add mayonnaise and honey to desired texture and taste.
Add a pinch or two of garlic. Mix in salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken and wine sauce
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and sherry together. Lay chicken breasts in a 9x13 casserole dish. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix 1 cup warm water, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons instant potato flakes.
Add to yeast mixture.
Put in glass jar with lid.
Let sit all day with lid closed.
Then refrigerate for 3 to 5 days.
Remove from refrigerator and feed it with 1 cup warm water, 2/3 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons of potato flakes.
Let mixture set at room temperature all day.
Starter is now ready to use.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries into hot Jell-O.
Cool until thick, about 45 minutes, then fold in Dream Whip.
In large pan, put in layer of cake pieces, then pour half of Jell-O over cake, add another layer of cake pieces.
Pour remaining Jell-O over top.
Chill until served.

title: bride's salad
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk.
Cook slowly until spoon films over.
Cool.
Add juice of lemon.
Fold in whipped cream.
Drain and combine the cherries and pineapple chunks.
Add marshmallows. Top with whipped cream mixture.
Stir gently.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. set aside.
Beat eggs, mix in shortening, sour cream and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients, add raisins, and stir until all flour is moistened.
Mixture will be sticky.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 min. using small loaf pan or 8-inch square or round pan.
Also before baking sprinkle some sugar over the top.

title: apple struedel
directions: Pour apples in baking dish. Sprinkle spice cake mix on top of apples and nuts.
Pour melted butter on top of all ingredients. Bake at 325° until bubbly.
Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: pasta soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, heat chicken in broth to boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and cool.
Add remaining ingredients to broth.
Heat to boil.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, or until macaroni is done. Remove chicken from bone and cut in bite size pieces.
Add to soup; cook 5 more minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until brown and solid.
Half the recipe for only 1 pie.

title: shortbread
directions: Sift sugar and flour together 3 times.
Place butter in a bowl and break it into chunks with fingertips.

Work in the flour and sugar mixture, a little at a time, until the mixture resembles cornmeal. Turn the dough out on a floured board and knead until it begins to crack. Roll it out 3/8-inch thick. Cut into triangles and put the triangles on baking sheets. Bake the shortbread in a moderately slow 325° oven for 20 minutes or until it is very lightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix equal parts of Elmer's glue and liquid starch; knead.
You may have to add more glue and knead some more.
Can add food coloring.
Store in an airtight container.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder
and
salt.
Beat
egg and add milk.
Combine mixtures and roll out on floured surface and let dry 2 to 3 hours.
Break
in
small
pieces
and
drop in 2 quarts of boiling broth and do not cover but simmer 45 minutes.

title: chicken poppy seed
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water until tender; bone, cut and put in casserole.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over this.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown (not very long) at 350°.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese, dressing, sour cream and dill weed until it looks like frosting. If too thick, add a little milk.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chop very fine broccoli, cauliflower and carrots and sprinkle on top of dressing.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: egg and sausage breakfast dish
directions: Mix ingredients and let sit overnight in a 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
This is great for a Sunday brunch.
Serves 6.

title: rich sweet pie shell
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Press into two 8-inch pie plates.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken elia
directions: Place chicken breasts in a shallow baking dish.
Drizzle with honey.
Sprinkle with rosemary.
Pour the lemon juice and then the soy sauce evenly over the chicken.
Place orange slices randomly in the pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes and then broil until the tops are somewhat blackened.
Serve over wild rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and oil.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add to flour mixture.
Stir in cinnamon and prunes (cook prunes that have been cut up; do not leave too much juice in the prunes).
Mix in nuts and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb 8 minutes in small amount of water; add pineapple juice and bring to a boil.
Add jello and sugar and cook until dissolved.
Add apples and pecans.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and salt in the top of a double boiler over hot water.
Cook over simmering water, stirring until well blended and heated through.
Add crabmeat, drained and flaked.
Transfer to chafing dish and keep hot over low heat.
Serve with bite size pastry shells, toast points or bland crackers.
Serves 20.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Spread butter or
margarine on bread.
Arrange 4 slices of bread in a greased
x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of the cinnamon.
Repeat, making 2 more layers.

title: baked stew
directions: Mix together.
Put in roaster or Dutch oven with tight lid. Bake at 275° for 5 or 6 hours.
Don't brown the meat.
Don't look at the stew until done.

title: killer chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in water seasoned with garlic salt and pepper until tender; reserve 2 cups of broth, then cut meat into bite size pieces.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil until tender.
Combine sauteed vegetables, chicken, tomatoes, pimentos, mushrooms, olives, chili powder, hot pepper sauce, salt and pepper in a large casserole.
Boil spaghetti in reserved broth and 3 1/2 quarts of water.
Cook until al dente and drain.
Fold cooked spaghetti and 4 cups of cheese into chicken mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with chopped pimento and set aside. Dissolve jello in hot water. Let cool.
Add nuts and celery to cheese mixture.
Mix into cooled jello stirring well.
Fold in whipped cream and chill completely.

title: corn-sausage chowder
directions: Cook sausage and onion. Drain on paper towels. Cook potato cubes, sausage, onion and water until potatoes are tender (about 12 minutes). Add corn, evaporated milk and marjoram. Heat through and serve hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a bowl, mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces and roll in mixture.
Drop each piece in Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar and pour over everything.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: the chewy oatmeal cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: apple roll dumplings
directions: Cook water and sugar to thin syrup.
Roll dough about 1/8-inch thick.
Spread on this chopped apples. Sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg and roll as for jelly roll.
Slice about 2 inches thick and place in pan, flat side down.
Put lump of butter on each.
Pour over all thin syrup and bake in a moderate oven.
Serve with cream.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin.
Dip in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Pan-fry in oil until lightly browned and chicken is almost fully cooked.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Crush up tomatoes.
Add tomato paste, seasonings, salt and pepper to taste. Cook in saucepan for about 15 minutes to blend flavorings.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with Mozzarella and bake again until cheese melts.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pudding and undrained pineapple.
Add marshmallows, walnuts and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine pudding, pecans and sugar.
Place dough in well-buttered Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter over dough.
Sprinkle pudding mixture over dough.
Leave dough out overnight.
The dough rises by morning.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: cherry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cold water and other ingredients.
Chill until firm in 9 x 13-inch dish or 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
When firm, frost with topping.

title: frozen brandy alexanders
directions: Beat with electric mixer and freeze in ice cream pail.
Nice to have on hand for the holidays.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Spread this over cake while it is still warm. Cover cake with foil and let cool until ready to serve. Cut in squares.

title: taco casserole
directions: Spray pie pan with nonstick spray.
Roll out biscuits to form a thin crust.
Brown ground meat; drain.
Add water, taco seasoning and tomato paste.
Add to crust, alternating with the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
When it starts to jell pour over pineapple and cottage cheese.
This salad can be put in jello mold.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, half of Parmesan, oregano, garlic salt and pepper. Roll chicken in mixture and arrange in a greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over, bake another 20 minutes.
Blend soup and milk, pour over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more or until done.
Sprinkle with a bit more paprika and serve.

title: white cucumber strips
directions: Cut into strips from center of peeled cucumbers (avoiding large seed) to measure 7 pounds.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion until browned; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except buns.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill buns with beef mixture.
For saucier Sloppy Joes, use 1/2 cup catsup.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Blend jello and cottage cheese well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla extract. Pour into pastry shell;
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 40 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: easy sticky buns i
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place frozen rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle pudding on top of rolls.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar; bring to boil and drizzle over rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap (if you butter the wrap a little, it won't stick).
Just leave on counter overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Saute 1 dozen tortillas on both sides in safflower oil, just briefly;
stack on plate.
In a skillet put 2 tablespoons safflower
oil
and
saute	onions,
broccoli,
mushrooms
and garlic.
Transfer to
a
bowl and add chopped olives, cilantro and 2 cups Jack
cheese;
toss and set aside.
In bowl combine enchilada and tomato
sauce;
pour	only
enough
to cover the bottom of a
pie tin.
Ready your attractive serving dish with a bit of
safflower
oil
and
tablespoons sauce.	Take one tortilla, place in	pie tin in sauce. Dip both sides, transfer to serving dish.
Place
large
spoonful of filling and spread evenly over tortilla.
Top
with
another	tortilla
dipped in sauce and repeat
filling.
Continue	until
all tortillas are used
up. Brace
with
toothpicks
as
necessary.
Top
with tortilla dipped in sauce.
Dribble remaining sauce over stack. In dish surround stack
with
refried
beans.
Top stack with round of foil and bake
30 minutes at 350°.
Last 15 minutes, top with Jack cheese and more sauce to baste.
Serve with sour cream, avocados and
a simple
iceberg lettuce salad. Mexican rice would be nice too! Don't forget Mexican beer.

title: fresh corn custard(when kids snub veggies.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter 10 x 6-inch shallow baking dish.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Brown both sides of chicken breasts in butter; set aside.
In same skillet, saute onion and green pepper, which have been cut up in large chunks.
Add cut tomato; saute for about 1 to 2 minutes. Put chicken back in pan; place a slice of cheese on each chicken breast.
Spoon vegetables over chicken; sprinkle 1/4 cup capers over entire mixture.
Put lid on; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil ingredients together for 1 minute; stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups quick oatmeal.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a large bowl. Cover with lid or plastic wrap. This salad keeps for several days in the refrigerator. It is better the second day.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon on cookie sheet and press with wet fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: california pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Beat egg, milk and salt together.
Blend into macaroni and spread on greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon on spaghetti sauce. Top with pepperoni, onion, mushrooms, olives and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: christmas leather
directions: Combine applesauce and thawed reconstituted juice concentrate. Cover oven-resistant dinner plates with squares of plastic wrap. Spread 1 cup of the applesauce mixture on the plastic on each plate.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes over low heat.
Stir frequently.
Beat egg yolk with 2 tablespoons of milk and add slowly to hot rice.
Stir fast and remove from heat.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Stick cloves in peeled orange.
Place on foil lined pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients in large pot and bring to a simmer. Remove orange from oven.
Discard cloves and add orange to punch.
Serve.

title: mom's shaggy dogs
directions: Place golf ball sized cookies two inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6-8 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen cookies.
Do not try to cut in half.

title: cranberry marble salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Allow to thicken and pour into jello mold, layering jello with sour cream.
Run knife through layers to give marbled appearance.
Allow to set.

title: thumb cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans or peanuts and flour; mix well.
Make into balls and put onto cookie sheet.
Press thumb into middle of cookie, making an indentation.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with icing, colored, or flavor of choice of jam.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage; cook over medium heat.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Stir in flour; cook until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk and seasonings.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and salt until completely blended.
Add butter and buttermilk.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Cut bread loaf or rolls in halves, lengthwise.
Spread with butter. Brown beef and drain. Combine with Parmesan cheese, seasonings, onions, tomato paste and olives.
Spread mixture on cut side of bread loaf or roll. Place loaves or rolls on cookie sheet. Top with tomato slices.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with cheese slices and return to oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Mix all together.
Heat at 400° for 20 minutes to meld flavors.

title: taylor's favorite:  pepsi pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot or slow cooker.
Serve over rice. Great
on a cold night!

title: vidalia onion au gratin
directions: Peel and slice onions; cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Add margarine to large frypan.
When melted, add onions and water.
Salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender-crisp.
Add flour and stir in well.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and milk.
Cook until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Put in greased casserole and top with more cheese or bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Place peppers on baking sheet.
Boil 4 to 5 inches from heat, 5 minutes on each side, or until entire surface of each pepper is blistered and blackened slightly.
Cut each pepper lengthwise into eight strips.
While still hot, scrape off skin with sharp knife. Remove ribs and seeds.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly and make into small balls the size of a large marble.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix together all ingredients.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs, dotted with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs together well. Add sugar and continue to beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to oil mixture alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in poppy seed and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or one Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef and broccoli with soy sauce dressing
directions: In large salad bowl, combine broccoli, beef, red pepper, mushrooms, bean sprouts and water chestnuts; season with pepper. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over salad just before serving.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef into cubes.
Cook
beef
in
a
skillet
until brown. Cut carrots, celery
into
chunks, chop up the onions. Salt and pepper to
taste.
Put
vegetables into saucepan with browned beef, add water
to
cover.
When
partly
cooked, add potatoes (cut into chunks).
Boil
until meat and potatoes are fully cooked, then add tomato paste.
Stir in and let cook for about 5 minutes.
In
skillet
put
bacon drippings and flour. Stir until flour is browned.
Add to stew to thicken.

title: fruit salad or topping for cake
directions: Mix together and serve over pound cake.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and sugar; cool.
Add unbeaten eggs and mix well. Add other ingredients.
Bake in a greased shallow pan at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: jane's heavenly salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, pour into shallow dish and refrigerate overnight. Drain pineapple, then fold together with cottage cheese and marshmallows.
Whip cream until stiff, adding 1 teaspoon sugar as cream is whipped.
Set aside.
Cut Jell-O into 1/2 to 3/4-inch cubes and remove from dish carefully with spatula.
Fold Jell-O into cottage cheese mixture.
Carefully fold whipped cream into the other ingredients.

title: saturday night chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Season to taste.
Mix soup and cream together; pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: annie baker's peach cobbler
directions: Mix well.
Chill for 4 hours.
Roll crust to desired thickness.
Cut in strips and cover cobbler.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix together in a quart jar the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Alternate the onions and cucumbers, adding a pinch of salt and pepper after each layer.
When the jar is filled, cover with the top and shake.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.
They will hold their flavor and consistency 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Put into a large pan or pot with water, salt, pepper and beef bouillon cube and Italian seasoning.
Cook slow for several hours.

title: tex-mex fondue
directions: Heat tequila and garlic in medium saucepan or fondue pot. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 minute.
Add cheese spread and lime juice; stir until cheese spread is melted.
Stir in cilantro.
Keep hot while serving.
Dip cooked chicken chunks, jicama chunks, red, green or yellow pepper chunks and tortilla chips into the mixture.

title: homemade cornmeal tortillas
directions: Mix in bowl, beat with beater until smooth.
Spoon 3 tbsp. batter onto a medium hot ungreased griddle.
Turn tortillas when edges begin to look dry, not brown.
Bake other side.
Makes 12 tortillas or crepes.

title: he-woman hot dish
directions: Make meatballs from hamburger and sausage.
Brown in oil; drain.
Add to drained noodles.
Add peas, carrots, tomato sauce, cubed cheese and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon torte
directions: Beat room temperature egg whites until stiff, but not too dry. Add vinegar, then sugar, slowly.
Beat until very stiff.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 275° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let meringue shell cool completely.
(When it comes out of the oven, meringue will be as high as baking dish, but upon cooling, will sink down in dish, forming a "crust.")
While meringue is cooling, prepare pie filling as on box, except where box tells to use 2 egg yolks in with the pudding, use the 5 egg yolks you have reserved.
Remove pudding from stove and stir in 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Put aside to cool well.
Spread 1/2 Cool Whip on cooled meringue.
Spread lemon pudding over Cool Whip. Spread rest of Cool Whip over the pudding.
Sprinkle with the chopped nuts, if using them.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: heavenly sunshine cake
directions: Mix all this and pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls. Roll in finely chopped nuts (if desired) or sprinkle with dill seed.

title: fat ladies
directions: Cut cookie dough 1/4 inch thick and press into 9x12x3 inch pan.
Bake at 325 for 20 minutes until light brown.
Cool slightly.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and spread with caramels that have been melted in cream.
Top with pecans and refrigerate. Cut into squares. Makes 24 Squares.

title: lemon frost pie
directions: Mix ingredients and press into dish like a graham cracker crust. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt cheese and mayonnaise over low heat. Add bacon and onion. Pour over thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover lightly. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Stir once.

title: raw apple roll
directions: Use a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Make biscuit dough for about 8 to 10 biscuits.
Roll out.

title: creamy basil fettuccini
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package.
Drain and immediately toss with oil, garlic and yogurt.
Add Parmesan cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados; mash with a fork.
Add the next 4 ingredients. Mix in enough mayonnaise to make paste.
Add lemon juice, salt, red pepper, chili powder and cumin to taste.
Serves 10 to 12 when used as a cocktail dip.
Serves 8 when used as a salad.

title: cajun chicken strips
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first six ingredients.
Add chicken, half at a time, and shake to coat.
In a large skillet, cook chicken in butter for 8 to 10 minutes or until the juices run clear.
Garnish with parsley and peppers if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: barbecue chicken in a bag
directions: Cut fryer then add
salt and pepper.
Combine all sauce ingredients
and dip each
piece
of
chicken
in
the
sauce. Grease a brown paper
bag
inside
with
vegetable oil.
Place chicken in the bag, skin
side down.
Pour the remaining sauce in the bag.
Fold tightly
and
place
in roaster with lid and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes at 350°.
Then put lid on and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in 1-quart measuring cup.
Microwave at High 1/2 minute or until melted.
Blend in flour and seasoning.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.

title: hot tuna canapes
directions: Mix tuna with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Add olives.
Add a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on toast strips and sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together zucchini, onion, and salt. Let stand overnight. Rinse well and drain.
Mix all other ingredients with zucchini mixture in a pot. Bring to a slow boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into glass jars and seal (do not process).

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Bring to rapid boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and cinnamon.
Pour in greased cookie sheet (16 x 11-inch).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Ten minutes before cake is done, start frosting.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain all the fruit; mix together in large bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: mango chutney
directions: Boil the sugar and vinegar for 5 minutes.
Then combine all the ingredients and simmer until the fruit is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: chess pie cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and press down.
Beat next 3 ingredients, blending well.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares. (Sprinkle top with additional nuts, if desired, before cooking.)

title: consume rice
directions: Saute dry rice and onion in butter until rice turns dark brown. Dissolve bouillon cubes into 2 cups hot water and add salt and pepper to taste for 1 cup rice.
Mix all in a covered dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coffee braid
directions: Add scalded milk to sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm, then add cake of yeast.
Add eggs, flour, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Knead lightly on floured board, place in a greased bowl and let raise double, approx. 2 hrs.
Punch down and let raise for 1 hour.
Make dough into 2 braids and let raise double again.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.	Spread with blended powdered sugar and brown sugar icing while hot.

title: dietetic apple cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and 1 packet of Sweet Mate. Simmer over medium heat until all water is absorbed. In a large bowl, combine oil, apples, applesauce, eggs, prunes, cinnamon, allspice, vanilla, 8 packets Sweet Mate, salt, soda and flour.
Mix well. Pour into a
9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is light brown.

title: janet's calico relish
directions: Cut green and red peppers into quarters; remove seeds.
Peel and quarter onions; grind carrots, green and red peppers and onions through food chopper (coarse).
Place in kettle.
Cover with boiling water.
Stir in sugar, salt and vinegar.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yield: about 8 to 8 1/2 pint jars.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg, stirring to blend.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.

title: sunny silver torte
directions: Set gelatine to soak in cold water.
Beat egg yolks, lemon juice, rind and 1 cup sugar.
Place in double boiler and beat until firm and creamy.
Remove from stove and add the gelatine; let cool.
Beat egg whites very stiff and add remaining cup of sugar. Fold in cooled yolk mixture.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Cream sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on tortillas.
Roll tightly and wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate all night or several hours.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: baked turkey
directions: Clean and prepare turkey as necessary.
Salt and pepper. Quarter unpeeled apple and peel onion.
Place apple pieces and onion inside turkey.
Place in roasting pan with tight fitting lid. Melt oleo and pour over turkey.
Add water to pan.
Cover pan and place in the oven that has been preheated to 475° to 500°.
Bake 1 hour and turn off.
Do not open oven door.
Leave in oven overnight or until oven cools completely without opening door.
Perfect turkey every time.

title: lizzies
directions: Soak raisins in bourbon overnight. Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Mix butter, brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Add to flour mixture. Stir in raisins and bourbon. Add pecans and candied fruit; mix well. Coat muffin tins with cooking spray (do not use liners). Fill with mixture. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: ground beef and tater casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and drain.
Combine beef, green beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon potato mixture in a ring around top outer edge of dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles overnight.
Turn jar upside-down in colander in sink.
Next day, in a large bowl, mix sugar, Tabasco and garlic until pink.
Layer ingredients back in jar, starting with sugar. All will go in jars with a little packing.
Screw lid on jar and let sit for 5 days, turning jar over each day.
After 5 days, pack pickles in sterilized pint jars, covering with syrup and sealing with sterilized lids and screw tops.
No hot water bath needed.

title: betty's delight
directions: Combine and mix well the flour, margarine and chopped nuts. Pat into bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: apricot mandarin sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender, blend until smooth.
Just before serving, warm sauce over hot water, stir in brandy and rum. Serve over ham or pork.

title: divinity candy(use candy thermometer)
directions: Cook together 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup light corn syrup.
Cook to 246°.
While this is cooking, prepare a second mixture in another saucepan using 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
When the thermometer is removed from the first mixture, put in second mixture and cook to 255°.
While the first mixture is cooking, beat egg whites stiff.
Pour boiled syrup, hot, directly on the egg whites, beating constantly.
(Eggs should be at room temperature and syrup added slowly.)
Do not scrape syrup from saucepan.
As soon as the first mixture is added to the egg whites, the second mixture should be cooked and ready to add, same as before.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat until when touched the candy does not stick to your finger.
Spread into a buttered pan and cut into squares.
This will keep well in the refrigerator or ships well in a wax-lined tin box.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in large casserole dish.
In mixer combine other ingredients and mix to a crumbly stage.
Spread over apples and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jelly pie
directions: Beat yolk of egg
good;
add
sugar,
butter, flour and jelly. Beat white of egg until stiff
and fold in.
Cook in a slow oven.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add blueberries in water. Mix thoroughly and cool to room temperature.
Set aside.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix potatoes and milk together, then add remaining ingredients.
Fry in about 1/4 inch shortening.
When brown on one side, turn.
Good with sour cream or stewed tomatoes.
If you fry in bacon drippings, use only 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Set the oven at 375°. By teaspoonful place on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: tuna ramekins
directions: In saucepan, blend soup, milk and sherry.
Add asparagus or peas and tuna.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Serve in 3 individual dishes.
Garnish each serving with croutons.

title: soda cracker chocolate candy
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with foil.
Grease.
Place crackers on foil.
Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn off oven.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over crackers.
Return to oven until chocolate is melted (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove using buttered spatula; press nuts into chocolate.
Cut in 1-inch squares while warm.
Cool.
Remove from foil.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer cauliflower, lettuce and bacon and cover with Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Leave covered overnight in refrigerator.
Before eating, stir and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Step 1:
Cook cabbage 5 to 6 minutes.
Do not overcook. Drain.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Place defrosted berries, sugar, lemon juice, egg whites and salt in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed 15 minutes until mixture is stiff and holds shape.
Whip cream, add vanilla and fold into berry mixture.
Pile lightly into baked shell.
Freeze overnight. May be garnished with fresh berries just before serving.

title: lima beans with sour cream
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together until onion is clear. Add sour cream; heat to boiling point, but do not boil.
Cook frozen limas until done.
Drain and add to sauce.

title: chip dip
directions: Combine ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: oodles meat loaf
directions: Before opening, break up the noodles from package into small pieces and combine in a mixing bowl with the seasonings from the flavor packet, chopped onion, chopped celery, chopped parsley, tomato sauce and beaten eggs.
Stir together and mix in 1 1/2 pounds lean ground beef.
Shape into a firm loaf in a buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes before slicing. Serves 6.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, saute garlic in oil (do not brown).
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add meatballs or any other leftover meats (pork, sausages, steak, etc). Simmer at a low flame for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent sauce from sticking to pan.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix together all ingredients at once.

title: surprise vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir until well blended. Serve warm or cold.

title: stuffing hot dish
directions: Mix seasoned bread cubes as directed on package; set aside. Brown and drain beef; season with pepper and onion to taste. Spread meat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add 1/2 can water to 1 can soup; pour over meat.
Pack bread crumbs over meat; poke holes (using long-tined fork) in stuffing mixture.
Add 1/2 can water to second can of soup; pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: o' henry candy
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter and nuts.
Add cereal and mix well.
Put ingredients into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together. Spread on top of cereal mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and broccoli in margarine.
Add mushrooms, cheese, soup and rice.
Stir over low heat.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes with skins left on.
Cut potatoes round.
Line up in greased baking dish.
Melt oleo in small pan and add Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt and pepper.
Pour this over potatoes.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: yorkshire pudding(serves 4)
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a bowl.
Mix the milk, water and egg together and gradually beat into the flour.
Mix until the batter is smooth and lump free.
Leave to stand for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fettuccine
directions: Mix in spinach, sour cream, cream cheese and cottage cheese. Add this to cooked and drained noodles.
Add Jack cheese but save a little for top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Salt to taste.

title: glazed strawberry yogurt squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick, 1/4 cup sugar and butter with fork until crumbly.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumb mixture; firmly press remaining mixture in bottom of ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until light brown.
Mix remaining ingredients, except Fruit Roll-Ups.
Pour over baked layer. Completely cover top of yogurt mixture with Fruit Roll-Ups, cutting to fit if necessary.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Return to oven; bake about 20 minutes longer, or until pick comes out clean when inserted into the center.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: teriyaki flank steak
directions: Trim excess fat; place steak in a shallow container.
Combine next 8 ingredients, stirring well; pour marinade over steak. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill steak 5 inches from hot coals for 5 to 7 minutes on each side, basting often with marinade.

title: italian parmesan chicken
directions: Blend cereal, Parmesan cheese, flour and seasoning until fine crumbs.
Set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing and coat with cereal mixture.
Place in a shallow baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in casserole.
Sprinkle each with sage and pepper.
Top each with a slice of onion and tomato.
Sprinkle each with dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour vermouth carefully in dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: batter for fish or chicken
directions: Dip chicken or fish in batter.
Deep fry.
Tastes a lot like Long John Silver's.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the pumpkin, Milnot, sugar, pumpkin pie spice (I use 1 teaspoon vanilla also) and eggs together and pour into an 11 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with the yellow cake mix over the pumpkin mixture. Add pecans. Melt butter or margarine and distribute evenly over top. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: pecan-crusted salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Cover baking pan with foil. Combine pecans and next 4 ingredients. Dip salmon fillets into olive oil and then pecan mixture. Place in a single layer on the baking pan. Bake approximately 10 minutes until fish flakes.

title: designer chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, cream margarine, brown sugar and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chunks.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut stems from cabbage leaves. Boil in 2 cups water until wilted. Cool. In bowl combine beef, rice, onion, parsley and cut up tomatoes. Add salt and pepper. Place 1 Tbsp. mixture on each cabbage leaf and coil tightly. Stack in a flat pan. Combine lemon juice, 1 tsp. salt, water and tomato liquid from canned tomatoes. Pour over rolls. Cover and simmer on top of stove for 30 minutes.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternating with buttermilk, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake at 325° in a preheated oven 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.
(Bake in a cold oven 1 1/2 hours.)
Bake in a large tube Teflon pan; grease but do not flour pan.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Turn out and let sit with pan over until cold.

title: chicken rosemary("low-fat")
directions: Mix together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onions and celery and saute a few minutes. Add remaining ingredients and a little water. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: taco bake
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Spread in bottom of baking dish. Brown hamburger.
Add sauce, seasoning and corn.
Spread over Bisquick mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press rolls onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 13 minutes at 300°. Combine sour cream, cream cheese and dip mix in bowl. Spread over cooled crescent rolls. Sprinkle with vegetables and grated cheese.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Combine egg and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease until they float.
Turn as necessary.

title: incredible disappearing water bagel
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix yeast mixture into flour.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cook chocolate pudding as directed.
Stir in cake mix.
Spread in jelly roll pan. Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 to 35 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 pound hot butter until clear.
In large saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until dark brown.
Gradually stir in beef broth.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add sauteed onions, butter, water, soy sauce, salt, Tabasco, Kitchen Bouquet, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon cubes. Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Then cover and simmer for 30 minutes over low heat.
Pour into six individual soup servers and place slice of bread on top of each.
Cover each with shredded cheese. Heat under broiler until cheese is golden and bubbly.
Serve at once.

title: ranch style bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat in skillet until brown.
Drain and put in casserole pan; add chopped onion and shredded cheese.
Pour Ranch Style beans on top, then mix corn bread mix as directed on package. Pour on top of beans.
Put into oven and cook for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Add chicken and eggs.
Add crumbs to mixture and pat into casserole dish.
Cover top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Place ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring often for 10 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box and cut into 2-inch squares. Layer all ingredients; end the top layer with Cool Whip.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together; spread in bottom of tray.
Pour caramel-butterscotch sauce over cream cheese layer. Slice Delicious apples thin and arrange over caramel mixture or slice apples in dish to dip in mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken in large kettle with enough water to cover. Cool.
Debone, skin and chop into bite size pieces.

title: baked cheese potatoes
directions: Dip each potato chunk in melted butter, then Parmesan cheese. Place in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hour.
Turn as potatoes brown. May also add bacon to cheese before coating.

title: nameless pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients (except Cool Whip).
Pour into pie shells and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Mix together sauce ingredients.
Place chicken thighs in a baking pan.
Pour sauce over and bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning chicken twice during baking.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a plastic container with a tight fitting lid.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Into 1 1/2-quart pan, put sugar, eggs, shortening (size of a large egg) and evaporated milk.
Fill with water 1/4 from top of pan.
Put on stove and keep stirring until lukewarm.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna and onion with prepared macaroni dinner; spread in buttered oblong pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture in pan.
Place cheese slices over top.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until bubbly for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese and meat ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, ground wafer meat and garlic powder.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in either chopped walnuts or dried parsley.

title: tamale pie
directions: Sift corn meal into boiling, salted water in top of double boiler and cook over direct heat with constant stirring until just thick; cover and place over hot water and cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often. Cool slightly, then turn into greased 8-cup baking dish. When mush is almost cold, pat it out evenly around sides and bottom of dish, extending it a little above top of dish for rim after filling is added. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and vanilla, stirring well to make a smooth, creamy mixture, as you would for white sauce.
Bring to a slow boil and then add butter.
Serve, while hot, over biscuits.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash the tomatoes. Cut off the top and bottom. Slice thinly. Roll in meal and fry in bacon drippings until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel. Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Melt margarine and stir in corn flakes and put on top of casserole.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients sugar, water, oil and vinegar. Bring to a rapid boil.
Cool and pour over the vegetables that have been combined.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form 1 tablespoon of mix into small patty.
Fry in small amount of oil until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry-orange relish.
Add pineapple.
Let stand and serve.

title: soap balls
directions: Start with 1/2 cup soap flakes, pour into bowl.
Put 4 to 5 drops food coloring in 1/2 cup water.
Pour water gradually into soap flakes and form into ball with hands.
Amounts vary.
Can add ribbon and hang or use in soap dish.
Neat kids' gift.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine chicken and about 1/2 cup cheese.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Place about 2 or 3 tablespoons chicken-cheese mixture on the wide end of each triangle and roll to the point.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients on high speed until fluffy and spreadable.

title: prune-nut bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; stir gently.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients. Add eggs and oil to prune mixture; stir well.
Add dry ingredients; stir until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter flavored Crisco, 1 1\2 cup of sugar, eggs, and vanilla thoroughly in large bowl, at medium speed.(electric mixer)

Combine flour, cream of tarter, baking soda and salt. Stir into cream mixture. Mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls. Combine remaining 1\4 cup sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Roll balls into cinnamon, sugar mixture, coating. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 min. Remove to cool on wire racks.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: sweet surprise
directions: Break up angel food cake into bite size pieces and place in a 12 x 10 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Slice bananas over cake.
Add pineapple.
Mix pudding accordingly with skim milk and pour over cake and bananas.
Add pie filling.
Top with Dream Whip. Refrigerate overnight for best taste.

title: popsicles
directions: In a bowl, combine soft drink mix, jello and sugar.
Pour boiling water over and stir until dissolved.
Pour cold water over and stir until mixed.
Freeze in paper cups, ice cube trays or Tupperware popsicle containers.
Freeze. (May place a popsicle stick in before freezing.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Arrange a layer of potatoes and some onion. Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper. Dot with butter. Continue layers. Pour milk over all. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake covered for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: salami or summer sausage
directions: Be careful of your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When once selected, give your entire thought to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle.
Others constantly get them in hot water.
This makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
