Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: john paul's deer camp coffee
directions: Set pan of creek water on campfire.
Bring to boil.
Boil until there's nothing wiggling in it.
Throw in the two handfuls of coffee.
Boil until black, but still liquid.
Shake out the dirty rag and strain coffee into cups.
Enjoy!

title: beef and broccoli oriental(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: In a 10-inch frypan, brown beef cubes in oil.
Add water and simmer about 1/2 hour, covered.
Mix cornstarch with Tamaric and add to beef, increasing heat and cooking until sauce thickens.
Add more water, if necessary.
Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces and add to beef.
Cover and simmer over low heat until broccoli is tender and bright green.
Do not overcook broccoli.
Serve immediately.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Remove bacon from skillet; add onions and saute.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate (glass is best).
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions over the bottom of the pie plate.

title: meg's stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions, drain and cool. Mix cheeses, egg, parsley flakes, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. After mixing the ingredients, stuff into the cooled shells.
Place stuffed shells in large baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place into a tightly sealed container.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nantucket scallop chowder
directions: Melt butter.
Lightly brown onions in butter.
Remove onions. Cook scallops in butter 5 minutes.
Add boiling water, onions and potatoes; simmer 15 minutes more.
Season to taste.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 5.

title: millie's delight
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, melted margarine and chopped nuts; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss drained beans, onion and bell pepper. Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over beans. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: carolyn's mom's coconut pie
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients, except coconut.
Melt butter. Add egg yolks, butter and milk slowly to dry ingredients; cook until thick,
stirring constantly. When thick, add coconut (2 cups), mixing well.
Pour into cooked 9-inch pie shell.

title: lobster noodle casserole
directions: Slice each lobster tail in half lengthwise.
Cut same half of each tail into chunks.
For sauce, melt butter; stir in flour, salt, paprika, pepper, onion and Bitters.
Add milk and cream. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add wine and lobster chunks.
Mix in cooked noodles.
Put in 3-quart casserole; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Arrange lobster tails pinwheel fashion around top and brush with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Return to oven for about 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: knox blox
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox unflavored gelatine and Jell-O. Add boiling water, stirring, until gelatine dissolves.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: old-fashioned apple dumplings
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Gradually add milk, stirring to make a soft dough.
Roll dough out on a lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness, shaping into a 21 x 14-inch rectangle.
Cut dough with a pastry cutter into 6 (7-inch) squares.
Peel and core apples.
Cut in half.
Place one apple half on each pastry square.
Dot each with 1 teaspoon butter. Sprinkle each with 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Moisten edges of each dumpling with water; bring corners to center, pinching edges to seal.
Place the dumplings in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: amish starter
directions: Use glass or plastic bowls and wooden or plastic spoons.
Mix the ingredients.
If you put a top on, do not place it on tightly. Never refrigerate.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix veggies together.
Pour canning salt over veggies.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Drain in colander and rinse under cold running water.
Mix vinegar, turmeric, sugar, celery seed, pickling spice (tied in a cloth), pimentos and hot peppers. Add veggies and bring to a boil.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: lazy man pierogi
directions: Saute onions with butter.
Add mushrooms, drained, until cooked.
Mix in sauerkraut (drained) and noodles.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use 3 to 4 layers of heavy-duty aluminum foil to securely wrap the roast.
Spread the mushroom soup and the dry onion soup over the surface of the roast.
Seal it securely.
Bake 45 minutes per pound.
Unwrap roast; save the gravy.
Slice meat against the grain.
Top slices with gravy.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt butter in 3-quart baking dish. Mix soup, rice and water; pour on melted butter.
Place chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours.

title: bread dough art
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Gradually add water.
Mix into ball.
Knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Add water and/or flour to make silk smooth.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1/2 hour for every 1/4-inch dough.
This is not to be eaten, for craft projects only.

title: apples and noodles with sausage
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Wash, pare and cut apples; then slice.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in baking dish.
Place half of the noodles in the dish, then half of the sausage and then half of the apples.
Sprinkle with half of cinnamon and sugar that was mixed together.
Layer remainder of ingredients.
Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cauliflower pea salad
directions: Pull cauliflower apart in tiny pieces.
Microwave peas for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool peas and mix with cauliflower, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Will keep about 4 days in refrigerator.

title: summer pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Put slight amount of egg over crescent rolls.
Bake until golden, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool spread the beaten cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dry dressing over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle cheese last.
Keep refrigerated until eaten.

title: cole's slaw
directions: Mix it all up.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in loaf pan. Set oven to 400° and cook for 1 hour.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish; pour on top, but do not mix, the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and milk.
Put on top of the batter the peaches and juice.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: russian cream dessert
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, gelatin and water.
Remove from heat after dissolved well and hot.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in 1 cup thawed Cool Whip. Chill in a 1-quart mold or put mixture in parfait glasses with fruit.
Strawberries are especially good to layer with this mixture.
Sweeten berries some.

title: rotelle with broccoli and garlic
directions: Combine oil and garlic; simmer until garlic is golden.
Add broccoli and wine; bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour mixture over cooked noodles.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with other ingredients.
Form into a ball and chill.
Before serving, roll in chopped pecans.

title: rapid chicken in wine sauce
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry on paper towels.
Dredge chicken in flour and saute in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes on the first side and 3 minutes on the second side.
Reduce heat and add the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil to the skillet with thyme, rosemary, oregano and garlic.
Stir to distribute herbs evenly.
Add wine and chicken broth to the skillet and bring to a simmer.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve garnished with parsley.

title: fast and easy poppy seed cake
directions: Dump ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix on slow to combine for 30 seconds or so, then beat at regular cake mix speed (medium) for 3 to 4 minutes.
Put into a Pammed or greased and floured Bundt pan and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
After cake is cooled, dust with powdered sugar or drizzle with powdered sugar, vanilla and water icing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Or any combination of other fruits or vegetables (fresh green beans, frozen peas) a salad is possible.
Cut the apple, tomato and celery in small cubes.
Dice the onion and penny cut the carrot. If you have 1/4 to 1/2 golden raisins and some nuts (walnuts or pecans) chop them and add them.
I cut some fresh basil and add that to the "cornucopia."
Toss everything with honey-Dijon mustard salad dressing.
What a taste-bud treat!

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 1/4 cups mix.

title: asparagas casserole
directions: Place asparagas in a baking dish.
Mix flour, butter and liquid, and pour over asparagas.
Put a layer of hard boiled eggs, a layer of cheese and then a layer of cracker crumbs.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice carrots and cook until tender.
Chop onions and cook until tender.
Slice squash (1/2-inch thick) and cook until tender.
Mix vegetables all together.
Add the soup and sour cream and mix together.
Melt margarine and mix with Pepperidge Farm dressing.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in large pot.
Add rest of ingredients (do not drain canned items).
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together the oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: country broccoli casserole
directions: Grease bottom and sides of glass cooking dish (13x9), add cooked rice.
Put onion in skillet and saute, then add thawed broccoli, mushroom soup, milk, Cheez Whiz and salt.
Cook about 15 min.
Put this mixture over cooked rice and bake in oven at 350° until top begins to bubble.
Serves 8-12.

title: easy baked meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil (for easy cleanup).
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls using a heaping tablespoonful mixture for each.
Place 1/4-inch apart in the lined pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until browned and no longer pink in center.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, sprinkling salt over mixture. Stir and let set approximately 5 hours; drain.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and seeds.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumber mixture and boil approximately 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: pig in the blanket casserole
directions: Put cabbage, rice and ground beef in that order in a casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage, rice and meat and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dr.  pepper cake i
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring the Dr. Pepper to a boil.
Pour over the oats.
Let cool.
Cream together the shortening (or margarine) and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until mixture is fluffy. Sift together brown sugar, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in Dr. Pepper mixture and vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and spread topping over cake.

title: pineapple angel cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pineapple together- pour in oblong cake pan and bake for as long as directed on box directions.

title: taco pie
directions: Combine beef, onion, peppers, salt and pepper in a skillet; saute until meat is brown, stirring frequently to crumble meat. Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings to meat mixture.
Cook over very low heat for 10 minutes.
Add additional water, if desired.
Spoon into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Place cheese strips over meat mixture.
Combine cornmeal, flour, buttermilk and egg; stir until well mixed.
Spoon batter over meat mixture.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes, or until browned.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread*
directions: Mix together; pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: hearty hash
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil.
Add remaining ingredients
to onions
with
roast
beef
first; potatoes on top of roast. Cover
mixture
with
milk.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Do not stir.
Garnish with cheese if desired.

title: round steak deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over serving sized pieces of steak that have been browned.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons flour. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: cracker chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed crackers, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, parsley and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in butter, then dredge in cracker mixture.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle any remaining butter over chicken. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, then turn pieces and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes (depending on thickness of pieces).

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Grind peppers and onions.
Add boiling water until covered and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix 1 pint vinegar and 2 pints water.
Pour over peppers and onions; let come to a boil.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix 1 pint vinegar, salt, sugar and mustard seed.
Add to mixture.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in
vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in pineapple. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin pans half full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool about 15 minutes.
Punch holes in cake.
Combine milk, sugar and half of the coconut in saucepan.
Let come to boil and simmer 1 minute. Spoon over warm cake. Cool completely.
Add rest of coconut to Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: leftover fried chicken
directions: In a pan heat brown gravy.
While gravy is heating, stir in onion, green pepper and red pepper.
Continue to heat on a low fire for about 20 minutes.
Place fried chicken in the pan.
Spoon gravy over the chicken.
Heat for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Great when served over a bed of rice.

title: penuche
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until it cools slightly and thickens.
Add nuts and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Put into casserole dish and add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice all vegetables.
Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Be careful with salt as Spam is salty.
Cook for an hour or until potatoes are done.

title: kolache dessert (czech)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt oleo in about 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
In mixing bowl, mix and combine sugar, flour, baking powder; add the milk.
Pour this mixture on top of oleo.
Do not mix.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together. Makes a large salad.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine and let set in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Before serving, top with grated cheese.

title: sticky bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine sugar, butter, cinnamon and corn syrup in pan and beat slowly.
Knead loaves briefly, just until elastic, with kitchen scissors, snip dough into 1-inch pieces and arrange half (or 1 loaf) in a greased Bundt pan.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in pot 3/4 full of water.
Add 2 teaspoons butter.
Cook until done.
Combine flour, eggs and salt together in a large bowl.
Stir in tablespoons of water until dough is mixed together.
Do not get dough consistency sticky.
Roll out on floured board and cut in square or rectangle shapes.
Cook on medium heat until done.
Add black pepper, if you wish.

title: lazy pickles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in large plastic bowl; refrigerate for 2 hours (do not drain).
Add 2 cups sugar; stir well, then add vinegar, celery seed and other ingredients.
Stir well; keep in fridge.
Will keep up to 3 months.
I usually keep them in a gallon glass jar.
These are delicious!

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Mix 3 teaspoons (or to taste) with boiling water.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted oleo and sugar well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar and spread over pretzel layer, when cool.
Mix jello and boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Refrigerate until almost set, then pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and spoon into well-greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until browned.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine
chocolate
chips,
butter
and
corn
syrup in medium size
saucepan.
Stir
over
low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and sugar. Add
Rice Krispies
cereal, mixing lightly until well coated. Spread evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.	Cut into
1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 48 squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: thanksgiving peaches
directions: O, the comfort, the inexpressible comfort of feeling safe with a person.
Having neither to weigh thoughts, nor measure words, but pouring them right out, just as they are!!
Chaff and grain together.
Certain that a faithful hand will take and sift them. Keep what is worth keeping and with the breath of kindness, blow the rest away.
Amen.

title: chinese chicken 'n noodles
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil until done.
Add next 3 ingredients. Add snow peas, cover and simmer for about 3 minutes, until snow peas are done.
Cook noodles in boiling water, drain and pour over chicken mixture.
Toss.
Optional:
Saute chicken livers and pur in with chicken.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and put in pot.
Cover with water and boil until not quite tender.
Take chicken out of pot and boil down to one cup.

title: baked fish au gratin
directions: Place half of fish fillets in a greased 9 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Cover with 4 slices of cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with thyme and parsley.
Saute onion in oil over medium heat until lightly browned.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute and pour over fish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a large skillet; cook about 10 minutes.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Can place in crock-pot and cook all day.
Add mushrooms 10 minutes before done.

title: crawfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in aluminum Dutch oven (don't use iron pot, as black iron will cause crawfish or shrimp to darken).
Season crawfish or shrimp generously with Creole seasoning or salt and pepper.
Add paprika to margarine.
Saute crawfish or shrimp about 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish or shrimp; set aside.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: In a blender mix bananas, orange juice and lemonade.
In a gallon container mix water, sugar and pineapple juice.
Stir in banana mixture.
Freeze mixture.
About 3 hours before serving, take out of freezer to thaw.
Add Sprite immediately before serving.
Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: crowd pleaser casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook green pepper in oleo.
Stir in tomatoes, water, herb spice mix and grated Parmesan.
Add spaghetti, chicken and 1/2 pound cubed Velveeta.
Mix and pour into a 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out and top with cheese slices.
Cut in half diagonally.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
May be assembled and refrigerated overnight.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage as for stir-fry.
If you like your cabbage tender, cook for a while before starting your casserole.
Place cabbage in casserole dish.
Mix celery soup with 1 can of water; pour over cabbage.
Crumble corned beef over cabbage and celery soup.
Mix mushroom soup with 1 can of water; pour over corned beef.
Make cornbread batter according to your recipe, adding a little more milk to make batter thinner.
Pour over casserole; bake until bread is as brown as you like it, about 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.

title: planter's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over crushed ice.
Makes 2 tall drinks.
Garnish with fruit, as desired.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together in 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1 roll of Ritz crackers, crushed and tossed with one stick of margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: dressing-turkey or chicken
directions: Crumble the cornbread and light bread into a large bowl.
Pour enough of the turkey or chicken broth over the bread to make a right consistency.
Stir and add other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased container or pour over a turkey or chicken and cook at about 400° until done.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Heat all together until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips. Serving suggestion:
Serve in a mini crock-pot.

title: chicken simon and garfunkel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pound chicken breasts until thin. Brush with butter, then sprinkle with salt and pepper. Lay chicken breasts on cheese slices and roll up (cheese on the outside). Combine egg and water. Roll chicken in some flour, then egg, then breadcrumbs. Fasten with toothpicks. Evenly space in a baking dish. Combine 1/2 cup melted butter and seasonings. Drizzle over chicken. Bake 30 minutes. Pour sherry over chicken and bake 30 more minutes. Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter toasted bread.
Cut toast into cubes and place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast, if desired.
Thoroughly beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, evaporated milk, boiling water and vanilla.
Pour over toast and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine remaining 4 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over bread.
Place dish in a shallow baking pan.
Pour hot water into pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Remove dish from water.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 8.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add powdered sugar, soft butter and vanilla and beat at medium speed 5 minutes.
Spread over crust and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Layer over egg mixture the crushed pineapple and sliced bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate for 6 hours.
Before serving, top with sweetened crushed strawberries and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook 10 minutes.
Add beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chutney-cream cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and cream cheese until creamy.
Spoon into bowl and refrigerate for several hours.
Makes 2 cups spread.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in one bowl.
Mix next 3 ingredients in another bowl.
Mix mixtures together well.
Knead well and roll out.
Cut into favorite shapes.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine all ingredients except peaches and boil 5 minutes.
Add peach halves and simmer for another 5 minutes.
Chill in syrup several hours or overnight.
Quick and easy and delicious with meats or on a party plate.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bake at 400° until brown.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Quarter mushrooms and saute with chopped onions until light brown, but still firm.
Mix together with other ingredients. Marinate for 1 day or overnight in refrigerator.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in skillet; drain.
Add spices, corn, tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Cover; bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Add rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir, then add shredded cheese.
Turn off; heat and cover for 5 minutes.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt the white chocolate and peanut butter in the top of a double boiler and melt the chocolate chips in another small saucepan over low heat.
Pour the first mixture in a foil-lined cookie sheet, then drop the chocolate mixture by spoonfuls on top and swirl until it's marbled looking.
Very simple, but very good.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, add pumpkin and eggs and beat well until mixed.
Add milk slowly while you mix. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° until a knife comes out clean. Makes one pie.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil water and
vinegar.
Pour
over
okra
in jars and seal. Let set for at least a week before using.

title: walnut fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in large saucepan.
Add milk gradually; mix thoroughly.
Bring to a boil on high heat, stirring continuously.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil mixture without stirring until small amount dropped in cool water forms soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and walnuts. Let cool at room temperature.

title: hobos
directions: Shape into patties and place on square of aluminum foil.
Place potatoes and onion on top.	Fold foil over and seal ends.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake squares
directions: Slice one roll of cookie dough and cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over layer of cookies.
Slice second roll and cover cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8-inch square pan. Combine butter and cocoa in medium-sized heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, egg, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Spread batter evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until center feels dry (do not overbake).
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows, walnuts and chocolate chips over top.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes more, just until topping is warmed enough to hold together. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: The advantage of this recipe is that you can make as little as one or two pints at a time as your cucumbers come from the garden, rather than waiting until you get a large amount.

title: potato casserole with onions
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add salt and pepper and cream cheese; beat.
Add eggs, flour, parsley and onions; mix well.
Put in 2-quart buttered dish.
Sprinkle onion rings and bake, uncovered, at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: impossible blender pie
directions: Put everything in the blender for one minute on high.
Bake in large 9-inch greased pie pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cauliflower morroco
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter with juice of 1 lemon. Saute cauliflowerets in butter with garlic, basil, salt and peeper to taste.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Wash chicken breasts; salt and pepper.
Cook rice.
Cook broccoli.
Saute vegetables with butter.
Mix rice, broccoli, vegetables, mushrooms, Cheez Whiz and soups.
Grease large dish with butter.
Lay chicken breasts on bottom of pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Last 15 to 20 minutes uncover and finish baking.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Puree all canned tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and spaghetti mix to ground beef on low heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Boil noodles.
Mix cottage cheese and eggs together. Layer beef, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and noodles, ending with Cheddar cheese on top.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange-date coffee cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Combine dates, orange peel and orange juice and stir into batter just until blended. Spread evenly in a greased 11 x 7 x1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Combine walnuts, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: This is a true English tart over 100-years-old from Paula's great grandmother in Essex, England.
Goes well with the English custom of afternoon tea.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut dates and pineapple into fine pieces.
Cut half of the cherries into 1/4 pieces and reserve the rest as whole.
Mix well and set aside.
Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder, mix well and add fruit and mix well.
Add pecan halves. Preheat oven to 275°.
Pour batter into 1 large tube pan that has be sprayed with oil.
Bake 3 hours or use 1 pound loaf pan and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt chocolate with condensed milk and salt.
Cook and stir until very thick and fudgy, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool 15 minutes.
Chill thoroughly, 20 to 30 minutes and then stir.
In a large bowl, beat 1 cup of whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with additional whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well. Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to batter and beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased (7 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Mix pineapple and milk together in a large bowl.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Fold in strawberry pie filling; add nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: shoo-fly pecan pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.

title: egg breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased pan.
Add a layer of cheese and a layer of ham.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Blend eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard and pour over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: old-fashioned sugar cakes in pie pans
directions: Beat
sugar and eggs together until sort of creamy; add milk and soda, then melted shortening.
Then add extracts and sifted flour.
Have
ready
(9-inch) pie pans, greased and floured; divide batter into 3 pans.	Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream together flour, butter and cream cheese.
Chill.
Roll out by hand 24 balls the size of quarters and press to fit tart pan.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, flour and egg together.
Pour over top of pie.
Let it set 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hershey's fudge
directions: Mix the sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk and stir until well
blended
and
bring to a rolling boil.
Turn down, but keep boiling
and
cook
to soft ball stage.
Remove from stove and add butter
and vanilla.
Let stand until butter is melted and mixture
is partly cooled.
Add nuts and stir until thick.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: easy sunday dinner
directions: Place everything in Dutch oven.
Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: crab scampi
directions: Rinse crab meat in cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook garlic and crushed red pepper 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Increase heat to high; add crab and salt.
Cook to warm crab meat; add tomatoes.
Heat through.
To serve, spoon onto warm platter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings, about 140 calories per serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake in a greased casserole at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve at once.
Especially good made with fresh corn.

title: 1 egg cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° in glass square for 25 minutes or glass 13 x 9-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Boil water for noodles.
Add bouillon cube.
Brown beef in oil with onion and garlic.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms; stir and cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; stir in.
Simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.
Stir in sour cream before serving.
Serves 6.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with fresh strawberries, pineapple, apples, grapes or other seasonal fruit.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt butter, then add cabbage, onions and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Brown hamburger, then mix ingredients together and bake until hot.

title: jungle sandwiches
directions: Slice bananas in half lengthwise.
Spread peanut butter on bananas.
Sprinkle raisins and pineapple on top.
Put bananas back together in sandwich form.
Slice into bite-sized pieces. Makes 24 servings.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup chicken broth in a small saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat until gelatin dissolves, stirring constantly, remove from heat.
Add remaining 1 cup chicken broth, lemon juice and horseradish.
Chill until consistency of egg white.
Stir in cucumber and next 3 ingredients; spoon into a 4-cup mold coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Cover and chill.

title: rice infallible
directions: Saute onion in margarine and mix with rice.
Add chicken broth.
Mix in casserole.
Cover and bake 20 to
30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind fruit.
Stir in sugar.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup water. Add fruit and mold.
Serves 14.

title: ground beef-noodle casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook ground chuck and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain.
Season with salt, pepper and celery salt, mixing well.
Return skillet to heat.
Add tomato sauce and oregano.
Reduce heat and let mixture simmer while noodles cook according to package directions.
Drain cooked noodles; stir into meat mixture.
Pour mixture into a greased shallow 10-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: watercress soup
directions: Liquify watercress and chicken broth; add asparagus and potatoes.
Blend; add salt and pepper.

title: marinated beet salad
directions: Combine beets with juice, vinegar and Equal in medium bowl. Cover lightly.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: cucumber dill crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss well.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops and clean peppers (save tops).
Chop to make 1/4 cup; set aside.
Cook the whole green peppers for 5 minutes. Invert to drain.
Sprinkle insides of peppers with salt.
In a skillet, cook beef, onion and the 1/4 cup chopped green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add undrained tomatoes, uncooked rice, water, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes until rice is tender.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread slices with butter.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage until brown; drain well.
Spoon over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese.

title: macaroni glorioso
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Saute onion, pimentos and mushrooms in butter.
Combine macaroni, onion mixture and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour on butter; do not stir.
Add fruit on top of this.
Add remaining sugar over this.
Do not stir. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and cinnamon; add to pineapple, nuts, sugar, baking soda and mashed bananas.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Mix well. Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Use tube pan or meat loaf pan.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in half lengthwise.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain well.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet; add juice and brown sugar. Stir until mixture thickens.
Add carrots to glaze mix and heat until carrots are heated through.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and flour together.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Let come to a slow boil.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar in small iron skillet.
Add slowly to mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla; pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake pieces of biscuits in a bag with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon until coated.
Place 1/4 of brown sugar and melted butter mixture in the bottom of a Bundt or tube pan.
Put a layer of 1 can of biscuits next, then another 1/4 of mixture, another layer of biscuits and so forth until all used up.
(You can also sprinkle any leftover cinnamon sugar mixture in between layers.) Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Empty from pan onto plate. May be torn apart or cut.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add granulated sugar and brown sugar to softened cream cheese. Add vanilla.

title: chocolate coconut cream pie
directions: In a small bowl beat egg whites with salt until frothy.
Spoon into shell, covering bottom.
Bake 5 more minutes and cool on rack.

title: hoppin' johns
directions: Combine bacon, onion and water in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add peas; cover and simmer for 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until peas are tender. Remove onion; discard.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: granola
directions: Heat oats in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: my mother's cocola cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients the next 3 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Beat batter until smooth, then fold in marshmallows.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread marshmallows around with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cuttin' muffins
directions: Mix cereal and orange juice in large bowl; let stand 2 minutes or until soft.
Mix in oil, egg and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except Streusel Topping.
Pour into greased muffin pans about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Sprinkle Streusel Topping evenly over warm muffins.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil muffins with topping about 5 inches from heat for about 1 minute, or until bubbly.
(Watch carefully to avoid burning.)

title: taco dip
directions: The night before, mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and dry taco mix together well.
Spread mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Allow jello to set and stir in drained pineapple.
Return to refrigerator and let jello congeal.
Combine together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix well and spread over jello.

title: hungarian cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in a large amount of boiling water until tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in sour cream and rest of ingredients.
Serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Process cream cheese and nuts in blender.
Add tobasco sauce, steak sauce and crushed garlic.
Mix together thoroughly and form into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with parsley.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into cakes.
Fry in shortening.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Pour juice from the cherries into a saucepan with the currant jelly, cornstarch and orange rind.
Cook over low heat until the jelly melts. Stir in the cherries. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: no-bake banana pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at low speed 2 minutes or until thickened.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Place roux in 5-quart casserole.
Add hot water, stock and chicken.
Stir in seasonings.
Cook on high 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese crisp
directions: Blend cheese and margarine on low speed of electric mixer. Add remaining ingredients and blend by hand (literally)! Roll in 1-inch rolls and chill or freeze in waxed paper.
Slice 1/2-inch thick and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed butter slices
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix and sift baking soda, flour, salt and spices.
Blend well.
Add poppy seed.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Mold into long smooth roll about 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil; chill several hours or overnight.
Cut in thin slices with a fluted vegetable slicer (or knife).
Bake on ungreased baking sheets at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cajun hush puppies
directions: Drop in preheated oil at 375° for 2 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil, peel and mash sweet potatoes.
Add butter, salt, egg, pineapple and pecans; whip lightly.
Mix in spices and brown sugar.
Roll into balls and press marshmallow into the center of each ball with thumb.
Close the opening and roll in coconut. Bake in buttered baking dish at 400° until balls are slightly brown.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: *Fat content of recipe depends on ingredients used.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease glass baking dish.
Place cherries in dish, followed by pineapple.
Add dry cake mix.
Spoon over melted butter.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour. Serve in custard dishes with whipped cream.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix sugar (both), shortening, peanut butter, egg and milk until smooth.
Add soda, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into balls (about 1 teaspoon); roll in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press candy kiss (unwrapped) in middle until sides crack.
Put back in oven for 2 to 5 minutes, until brown.

title: hot cinnamon bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Beat in salt and egg (well beaten), then add milk. Beat in flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Pour into a medium size well-greased pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture. Bake from 25 to 30 minutes in hot oven at 375°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in casserole (drained); spread soup (not diluted) on top of them, then spread onion rings. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 20 servings.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pears and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in paper bag.
Drop in beef, a portion at a time; shake until coated.
Mix with olive oil in 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Stir once.
Add onions, carrots, potatoes, celery, water and the tomato sauce with mushrooms; mix well.
Cover; bake at 350° for about 1 3/4 hours or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix fruit filling and pineapple, place in the bottom of an ungreased pan. In another bowl, mix pecans, coconut and cake mix. Place on top of fruit, evenly. Place sliced oleo on top of mixture. Bake at 350 for 1 hour. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: yummy cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, oil and egg.
Beat on medium speed until crumbly.
Stir in peanuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium bowl, beat condensed milk with peanut butter until smooth; spread over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cheese crock spread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° until puffy.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon lace cookies
directions: Mix the sugar and butter until light and creamy. Add the remaining ingredients; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are golden. Cool, then serve.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Add 1 (large) box
vanilla pudding to the liquid.
Cook and stir to a
full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tablespoon butter. Then add
fruit.

title: ann's cumin rice
directions: Melt tablespoon of butter in a heavy saucepan with tight fitting lid.
Saute the onion and garlic until onion appears glossy.
Add the rice, cumin, salt and pepper.
Stir briefly over low heat until the grains are slightly turning brown in color. Add broth, parsley, thyme and bay leaves.
Make sure there are no lumps in the rice.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer over low heat.
Cook for 17 minutes.
Discard bay leaves.

title: corn fritters
directions: Blend biscuit mix, sugar, egg, milk and salt; beat thoroughly. Fold in corn and drop by teaspoon in 2 inches hot fat.
Fry until brown.

title: old fashioned molasses candy
directions: *May use 1 cup molasses.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients until thick (about 5 minutes). Pour into prebaked pie shells.
Chill for 2 hours before serving. Makes 2 pies.

title: oven barbecued pork ribs
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Brown ribs on both sides.
Add sherry and 1/2 cup water.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all together and
pour into a graham cracker crust; chill in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Microwave morsels in microwave-safe bowl on Medium-high (70%) power for 1 minute. Stir. Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth. Stir in peanut butter until well blended. Add chow mein noodles and marshmallows; toss until coated. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto prepared baking sheet lined with wax paper. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fruit torte
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 9-inch buttered baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar or 1/2 cup chopped nuts over top. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together. Put this in a 9 x 13 pan which has been sprayed with Pam cooking spray.

title: amish cinnamon bread
directions: Stir ingredients well. Do not use electric mixer.
Pour batter into 2 large or 5 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour for large pan; 45 minutes for small pans.

title: friday night chili
directions: Combine ground beef, garlic and onions in a Dutch oven until beef is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer uncovered one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked zucchini and cheese
directions: Put zucchini in colander or on a towel to drain. Combine remaining ingredients. Add zucchini and mix well. Pour into a lightly oiled 2 quart casserole. Bake at 350 for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: snowball meltaway cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt and heat butter until light brown in color.
Pour in small bowl.
Chill until firm. Cream browned butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Gradually add flour.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated 325° oven. Roll into powdered sugar while still warm.
Cool on wire rack.

title: banana bread
directions: In bowl, mix flour, soda, tartar and salt.
Set aside.
In blender, put remaining ingredients; blend on high for 20 seconds. Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into 8 x 4-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg and milk into dry ingredients. Stir in apples and drop by teaspoonful into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, approximately 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels, then roll in powdered sugar or pour maple syrup over the fritters.
Makes 12 to 15 fritters.

title: glazed butterscotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In medium bowl, combine
mix, sour cream, egg and orange peel. Beat with wooden spoon, just until well combined.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Let cool slightly in pan on wire rack.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix sugar with butter and vanilla; add nuts and flour.
Form into about 24 balls.
Bake in medium oven (350°) until just dry throughout but not browned.
Carefully roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a shaker bottle.

title: plum jam
directions: Wash plums.
Crush and measure.
Combine plums and sugar in large pan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add pectin at once.
Skim off foam.
Stir jam for about 5 minutes.
Pour into glasses and seal at once.
Makes 8 pint glasses.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Drain fat.
In same skillet, add can of Spanish rice and tomato sauce or Ro-Tel.
Simmer in skillet on low for about 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together soup and water until smooth.
Melt margarine in a large casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture into casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces in dish.
Salt and pepper and place slice of cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake until chicken is done (about 45 minutes).
Remove from oven.
Place chicken pieces at one end of dish and add rice in other end.
Mix rice with juices; cover again and return to oven for 15 additional minutes.

title: rabbit scrabble
directions: Cover rabbit with water.
Cook until tender, then remove from broth.
Cool and pick meat off bones.
Add meat back to broth in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, add sage and onion (to taste) along with salt and pepper.
Slowly add cornmeal to boiling broth until broth thickens up.
(Do not completely cook in Dutch oven, just thicken.)
Kind of like wet cornbread dressing.
Pour in greased loaf pans.
Chill.
Slice and fry in small amount of cooking oil.

title: pecan cranberry spread
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat at medium speed and cream the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Transfer to a small bowl. Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until flavors blend at least 30 minutes. Serve cold with crackers.
Makes one cup.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour in a large bowl and chill.

title: old fashioned soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda and spices.
Melt shortening in saucepan large enough for mixing cookies.
Stir in sugar and molasses and cool.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Beat about 20 strokes.
Shape into ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until light brown.

title: liquid hop (jug) yeast
directions: Boil hops in water until strong.
Strain in malt flour and rub through a coarse cloth.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Stir in brown sugar.
Place in jug in warm room "to work the cork bottles tight."
Keep cold.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light, then add bananas that have been pushed through a sieve.
Add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven at 375° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes a 1 pound loaf.

title: coffee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Mix other ingredients together and add to other creamed ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly hash fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit of extra juice.
Mix all together the first 5 ingredients.
Blend in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Cut up some of the cherries to give color.
Spread on top small amount of Cool Whip; top with kiwi and cherries, cut in slices, of course.

title: t v snacks
directions: Mix cereals, pretzel sticks and nuts.
Sprinkle garlic salt and seasoned salt on dry ingredients.
Pour butter and Worcestershire sauce over dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into large pans. Bake at 300° for 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave mixture in oven overnight.
Cool; store in airtight containers.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and onion flakes.
Add cheese, tuna and noodles.
Stir with fork to distribute evenly.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients, except bread crumbs and mayo, thoroughly. Shake bread crumbs over mix.
Add mayo; shape.
Dip in egg and then bread crumbs.
Fry until brown.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery.
Add tomato paste, water, stock, wine, bay leaf, saffron, thyme, parsley, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in clams and clam juice.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add fish, shrimp, scallops, crab or lobster.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes longer until clams open.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together, making a runny dough.
Place in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and baste with melted butter.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Do not overbrown.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: leroy's elephant stew
directions: Brown gravy (lots of it).
Cut elephant into bite size pieces. This will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook over outdoor fire about 4 weeks at 465°.

title: glorified squash
directions: Add all ingredients to mashed squash as listed.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs (not listed).
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° until set.
Remove and top with cheese.
Cover with foil and set back in oven until cheese is melted.
Oven is turned off for this.

title: cold rice salad
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil; stir in rice and return to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Cool.

title: pizza hamburger pie
directions: Lightly toss beef with garlic salt, pepper, salt, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Press meat against sides and bottom of an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Spread tomato sauce over top surface.
Sprinkle with a little onion, oregano, red pepper and cheese.
Cook at 70% power for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Grease casserole and place layers in order named.
Salt each layer as desired.
Bake slowly in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken and cheese soup
directions: Brush both sides of chicken with lime juice. Sprinkle chili powder and cumin evenly over both sides; let stand 10 minutes. Grill or broil chicken until cooked through. Cool; cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: monkey bread
directions: Note:
Won't work with scratch biscuits (homemade).
May substitute 3 tubes of regular biscuits (10 count).

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place cooked broccoli on bottom.
Layer with cooked chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Place cubed bread in butter.
Place on top of cheese (like croutons). Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Delicious!

title: mexican omelette
directions: Take large skillet and on high, add oil then potato and onions.
When they start to brown, add egg and water.
When it starts to firm, add ham, cheese, sausage, pepper and tomato. Lower heat.
Slide out on plate to help you flip it.
Do not fold over.

title: beef marinade
directions: Marinate for 2 hours.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Spoon into ungreased pan. Stir in taco seasoning mix (dry), tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended; pour over beef mixture.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomato and shredded lettuce.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Roll into 1-inch balls or roll in hands to make small "S" shape.
Place on cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and if desired frost with vanilla frosting or sprinkle with nonpareils.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken and debone; save the broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter or oleo.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, peas and mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti in broth and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with spaghetti and place in casserole dish.
Layer the top with Velveeta and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheesy beef casserole
directions: Select extra lean ground beef.
Heat oil in a large skillet. Saute onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add beef.
Saute until pinkness is gone.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese, taco mix, sour cream and salsa onto a large pizza pan size platter.
Layer with the pepper, tomato, onions and cheese.
Surround outside of platter with ripe olive halves.
Serve with plain or cheese flavored chips.

title: cranberry glazed chicken breasts
directions: Combine flour and spices on waxed paper.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Place butter and onion in medium frying pan and heat over medium heat until butter is melted.
Add chicken and saute until lightly browned.
Combine cranberry sauce and brown sugar in small bowl.
Pour over chicken; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.
Nice served with rice cooked with chopped water chestnuts.

title: super bean pot
directions: Fry onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Grease 10 x 14-inch cookie sheet; line with wax paper so paper extends 1-inch over ends.
Pour mixture on top of wax paper.
Bake approximately 15 minutes.
Check frequently.
Cover a tea towel/dish towel with confectioners sugar.
Flip cake roll out on top of towel.
Peel wax paper off.
Roll long ways up in towel and refrigerate for 30 minutes or until cool.
Then unroll, cover with spread, reroll, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in another bowl the flour, oatmeal (blend oatmeal in blender before), salt, baking powder and soda.
Add flour mixture a little at a time to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, chocolate and nuts.
Bake 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 86 cookies.

title: joe's barbecued beef brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients except beef, mixing well.
Place meat in a heavy plastic bag and pour marinade over it.
Squeeze air from bag and fasten bag.
Place bag in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; marinate in refrigerator at least 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking casserole dish.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs.
Starting and ending with flour, mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix and add water to make 1 gallon.

title: crawfish file gumbo
directions: Heat oil in a large black pot.
Add flour to oil.
Make a dark roux.
Add celery and onions.
Saute 30 minutes.
Add water. Brown tomato paste in butter.
Cook until it loses its bright red color.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 can Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add this mixture to other pot and simmer 1 hour.
Add crawfish, crabmeat, green onion tops, bell pepper and parsley.
Adjust seasonings and simmer about 30 minutes.
This is a thin gumbo.
To thicken, add cornstarch, dissolved in water.
Serve over rice.
Add file to finished bowl.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to boiling point.
Mix flour and sugar; add to Coca-Cola mixture.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to batter.
It will be thin with marshmallows floating on top. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost while warm. See frosting recipe.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix these ingredients, except 1/3 can of tomato sauce. Pat out on foil. Put 1 1/2 cups grated cheese on this and roll.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour rest of tomato sauce and 1/4 cup of cheese on top. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: lucille's meat pie
directions: Over the entire surface of a beef or pork roast, make slits with a knife at about two-inch intervals and fill the slits with salt, cayenne pepper and slices of jalapeno and garlic.
Brown the roast in a pot on top of the stove.
Then add water to cook until tender, along with chopped bell pepper, celery and onion.

title: tin plate special
directions: Wash beans; cover with cold water and let soak overnight. Bring beans to a boil and cook 1 hour, drain, discarding water. Brown roast in hot shortening in a large Dutch oven or roaster. Add peppers and onions and cook until tender.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender and meat is done.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Heat 1/2 inch of oil in skillet and fry tortillas about 15 seconds each side; remove and pat off excess oil.

title: pork and beans bread
directions: Combine raisins and boiling water.
Stir and set aside to cool. Beat eggs, oil, sugar and pork and beans until beans are broken up. Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Then add cooled raisin mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased medium floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: our favorite meat loaf(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients except the ketchup; mix well. Press the mixture evenly into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Spread the ketchup over the top and bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until no pink remains and the juices run clear. Remove from the oven; drain and allow to sit for 5 minutes. Slice and serve.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a large saucepan, bring pineapple and syrup to a boil. Remove from the heat; stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in the buttermilk.
Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Pour into an 8-cup dish.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Beat until smooth. Pour into pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a dinner knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve together the sugar and 4 cups water. Bring to a boil. Mix all ingredients and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw mixture until slushy.
Add 3 large bottles ginger ale. Leftover punch can be frozen for later use.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix flour, sugar and salt.
In a separate dish, dissolve yeast in the warm water; add sugar and let stand for 10 minutes.
In a separate bowl, stir together melted margarine and milk.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture; mix well. Add yeast mixture to this and mix well.
Make a hole in the middle of the flour mixture and pour the liquids into the flour.
Mix well.
(You may have to add more flour to make dough softer, but the dough has to be elastic-like so it will not be sticky.)
Let rise.
When dough has risen, make a loaf and let rise again until the loaf doubles in size (approximately 1 hour).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough on pizza pan (may need to wet hands to spread evenly).
Bake according to directions on cookie package.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled cookie crust. Arrange cut fruit on top of cream cheese mixture.
Use pastry brush to spread apricot preserves on fruit as glaze.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut and serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water and set aside.
Beat shortening, sugar, molasses and egg until fluffy.
Add flour, spices and salt together.
Alternately add flour mixture, soda, coffee and raisins. Drop on greased cookie sheet by tablespoons approximately 1-inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Combine with peanut butter.
Mix until creamy and smooth.
Add sugars, flour, egg, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° or until golden brown around edges, 10 or 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Enjoy.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to a hard ball (265° on candy thermometer) or until small amount forms a hard ball in cold water. Pour syrup over stiffly beaten egg whites slowly, while beating at high speed with an electric mixer.
Beat until thick and creamy and stiff enough to hold shape.
Sift thick coat of powdered sugar on wax paper and pat or roll out candy while it is still hot to about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up like jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate 1 hour and slice.

title: whole wheat popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously grease 12 muffin pan cups (or spray with Pam).
Place in oven to heat 2 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, eggs, milk, crumbs, onions, salt, nutmeg and mustard.
Shape into 24 small meatballs, using about one tablespoon meat mixture for each.
Roll in flour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Quantity of cheese, milk and saltines depends on your individual taste.
Cook macaroni as direction states on box and drain well.
Lightly grease or spray with Pam a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Spread 1/2 of macaroni in bottom of dish.
Slice cheese and lay 1/2 of slices over macaroni.
Spread remaining macaroni on top of cheese, then cover with remaining cheese to complete second layer.
Crumble saltines and sprinkle over top. Add enough milk to cover both layers of macaroni.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until milk is set.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Add cheese.
Mix together.
Spread on cocktail bread.
Place under broiler a couple of minutes until bubbly.
Can freeze.

title: golden lasagna
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in melted butter in a 2-quart saucepan until tender (do not brown).
Stir in drained mushrooms, pimiento, soup, milk and basil.
Heat well.
Arrange 1/2 of noodles (cooked and drained) in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, then layer in 1/2 of Cheddar cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: bunny's punch
directions: Mix all together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 50 punch cup servings.

title: open apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour and put half of the crumbs in unbaked pie crust.
Save the other half to put over top of apples. Slice thin slices over bottom, then arrange halves upside-down and fill in with chunks.
Pour table cream over top.
Add crumbs. Sprinkle cinnamon over crumbs.
Bake in deep pie plate at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Place all of the ingredients, except the last four items, in a clear glass bowl in layers in the order given.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together, adding a little lemon juice to make mixture easier to spread.
Top with grated cheese and refrigerate.
Cover tightly.
Do put dressing on when you make the salad but do not mix until serving time.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in margarine.
Crush potato chips finely.
Mix all ingredients together and bake either in shells or casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle some of potato chips on top.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Pour in the Coca-Cola and stir well.
Put in refrigerator, uncovered, overnight.

title: fruit pizza - kid pleaser
directions: Mother placed slices of bread on broiler pan and spooned pork and beans on bread.
Put slices of cheese over beans.
Cut slices of bacon in half and put pieces on top of cheese.

title: date bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool, cut in small pieces and roll in granulated sugar.

title: ryan's migas
directions: Fry corn tortillas in oil.
When they turn crisp, add tomatoes and onion or picante sauce.
When soft, add eggs.
Amount of ingredients depends on taste and amount of eggs used.
You can also add shredded cheese just before serving.
I usually start with 4 tortillas.
Picante sauce depends on how how you like it.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle on garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Use oil and wine vinegar or Italian dressing is very good.
Chill for 30 minutes and serve.

title: apple raisin salad
directions: Plump raisins in hot water.
Drain and cool.
Toss apples with lemon juice.
Mix with raisins, celery, carrots and nuts. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Toss with apples and raisin mixture.
Serves 6.

title: orange blush
directions: Combine undiluted orange juice, cranberry juice and sugar. Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, stir in sparkling water and pur over crushed ice into old-fashioned glasses.
This can also be put into a punch bowl and an ice ring put into it.
Yields 6 servings.

title: glazed lemon bread (teacakes)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl. In another bowl, stir together melted butter, sugar, eggs, and almond extract. Add flour mixture and milk alternately to sugar mixture. Add lemon extract. Pour batter into 2 (5 3/4 x 3 x 2 1/8) small loaf pans or 1 loaf pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (small loaf pans) or 55 - 60 minutes (large loaf pan) or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Mix lemon juice and sugar well, immediately spoon over hot loaves/loaf. Cool for 10 minutes on a wire rack. Remove bread from pan; cool completely. Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: ground turkey stew
directions: *Try Oriental vegetables, green beans or broccoli.

title: pears with chocolate sauce
directions: Peel pears and cut them; remove cores.
Saute them in butter until tender and golden brown.
Serve warm with heated chocolate syrup.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Combine rest of ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Test for doneness.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour twice and add baking powder the second time.
Add vanilla to milk.
Use same cup for measuring all ingredients. Beat egg whites.
Cream the oil and sugar and add egg yolks.
Beat well and add milk and flour.
Mix well and fold in egg whites. Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: shrimp strawberry salad
directions: Brown 2 packages ramen noodles, almonds and sesame seeds. Add to onions, lettuce, strawberries and shrimp. Mix together with dressing.

title: polgaduitsa(roast sirloin with fried potatoes)
directions: Sprinkle sirloin or thin beef steak with salt; dredge in flour and sear in butter on all sides.
Place in roasting pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut roast beef into thin slices across the grain and serve with fried potatoes and drippings.
Sprinkle with finely chopped parsley.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix squash, sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and mix in.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute and stir.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Spray brown grocery bag (inside) with Pam.
Put in popcorn and pour syrup mixture over corn.
Put bag in microwave on High for 1 minute. Take out.
Shake well.
Put back in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake bag.
Pour in pan to cool.
Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: oatmeal burgers
directions: Mix ingredients together and
fry lightly on both sides. Add 6 cups hot water,
tablespoons
oleo, 1 tablespoon Vegex and 4 tablespoons soy
sauce.
Thicken
gravy
with
cornstarch slightly.
Cook on simmer about 45 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add unbeaten egg and flavoring.
Beat thoroughly.
Mix 1/2 cup flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk. Add your nuts mixed with flour.
Beat together.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate bar cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round baking pans.
In small bowl, stir together milk chocolate bar pieces, butter and water until chocolate is melted.
In large mixer bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add chocolate mixture, beating on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire racks.
Cool completely.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake fish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add fish and mix well.
Bake until firm.
Garnish with parsley sprigs and sliced hard-boiled egg.
Serve with Lemon Mushroom Sauce.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until well blended. Great with strawberries. Also cream cheese and a little honey makes a good dip. Can change the color if you want to with food coloring.

title: black bean pie
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic.
In a bowl, mix beans, sauteed mixture and cheese together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 425°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Slice or chop onion, celery and red pepper into fine pieces. Saut in butter until very tender.
The proportions of vegetables is optional, the goal is about 1 1/2 cups when raw.
Mix all ingredients together.
Take 1/2 cup proportions and shape into cakes.
Coat cakes with crushed saltines (crush one sleeve of saltines).
Place on a baking sheet; pour melted butter over top of each crab cake.
Bake at 450°.
Turn over after 10 minutes. Repeat until golden.

title: mothers bread pudding
directions: In a 2 quart casserole add eggs.
Add cornstarch dissolved in 1/4 cup milk.
Add sugar.
Stir in 6 cups milk.
Add nutmeg.
Add toast buttered lightly and cut diagonally.
Hold toast to bottom the mixture with a fork until saturated.
Bake at 350 degrees for 70 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients; mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients; beat well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While hot, spread with large jar Marshmallow Creme.
Cool completely.

title: easy baked haddock
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange fish in ungreased baking dish. Spread mayonnaise evenly over fish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over mayonnaise.
Bake, uncovered, until fish flakes very easily with fork and is opaque in center, 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges and fresh parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: *Can use buttermilk and light cream to reduce fat.

title: butter roll(1930)
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Pour on well-floured board or wax paper.
Roll thin with floured rolling pin about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut butter into small pieces; place evenly over dough. Pour sugar over butter.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, cooked broccoli, butter, onions, soup and Cheez Whiz together.
Place in large casserole dish or oblong pans and bake at 350° or 400° for about 40 minutes.
Add grated cheese on top and melt.
Let cool before you spoon out.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put ingredients into bowl as given.
Use Wesson or Crisco oil. Add plain flour last.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour. Bake in Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
You may top with a sprinkling of powdered sugar or powdered sugar, milk and vanilla (just to drizzle over top).

title: ham casserole
directions: Put spinach in microwave 4 minutes.
Drain water out.
Shred cheese.
Save 1/4 for top of casserole.
Add rest of ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water in percolator. In basket, put other ingredients with the cinnamon sticks being broken in pieces.

title: nancy's pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine biscuit mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, allspice and milk. Mix well until all bumps disappear.
Pour in the pumpkin.
Mix in the oil, eggs and vanilla.
Place oil in pan and cook until golden brown.

title: easy chocolate trifle
directions: Mix milk and Jell-O pudding. Beat with a whisk until well blended. Mix with 1 bowl Cool Whip. In a glass trifle bowl or punch bowl, layer first brownie cubes, second pudding mix on top of cubes, third strawberries on top of pudding and fourth 1 bowl of Cool Whip on top of strawberries. Can put strawberry halves on top of Cool Whip (optional).

title: hobo bread
directions: In evening, soak raisins in boiling water with baking soda. Cover.
In morning, add brown sugar, white sugar, oil, salt and flour.
Grease and flour four 1 pound coffee cans.
Divide batter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
