Place in saucepan and soak 8 hours or overnight in the water.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature. Cream and gradually stir in drained crushed pineapple until smooth. Add 1 cup of pecans, green pepper, onion and salt. Chill mixture well. Form into a ball and roll in remaining cup of pecans. Chill until serving time. Garnish with maraschino cherries and parsley. Serve with assortment of crackers.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Mix together other ingredients with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in medium pan.
Bring to boil and cook for 3 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Stir in morsels and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until cool and spreadable.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter together; press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: "out of this world cake"
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
When it's done, punch holes in cake (while hot).
Pour in Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping over top of cake.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: banana split cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cracker crumbs with melted butter. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks butter and beat 15 minutes.
Spread over cracker crumbs, then spread pineapple and bananas in layers.
Add a layer of whipped topping.
Sprinkle nuts on top; decorate with cherries if desired. Chill overnight.
Serves 16.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix as listed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix oleo, 10x sugar and peanut butter together.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix with hands and form to size desired.
Lay on cookie sheets on wax paper to harden (1/2 hour or longer).

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: You will need a heavy, 3-quart pan with one handle.

title: tuna rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and roll out dough about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread dough with tuna fish; roll up and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve covered with soup.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving the zucchini for last. Pour into small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Slice very thin.

title: ice cream topping
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa. Add sugar, adding only 1/2 cup at a time, stirring well after each addition and milk.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add 1 tablespoon vanilla. Pour into 2-pint size containers or 1-quart. Keep refrigerated.

title: pudding dessert butterscotch
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and the flour.
Mix together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: smothered beef and rice
directions: Have a large skillet or Dutch oven at roasting heat.
Cube meat and add to pan; meat will stick to pan, but will loosen as soon as it has seared.
Turn meat cubes and brown well.
Reduce heat to low, or finishing; add tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Cover and cook 45 minutes; add onions.
Replace cover and continue to cook for an additional 50 minutes over low, or finishing heat.
Serve meat and sauce over seasoned hot rice. Serves 6.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix together.
Spread on English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until bubbly.
Cut muffins into quarters.

title: grandma's white bread
directions: Pour boiling water over lard, sugar and salt.
Use large bowl. Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and let mixture cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add to other liquid.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Let rise to double bulk; knock down and let rise again.
Knock down and knead well.
Put in greased and floured bread pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
To keep crust soft, coat with butter while still warm from oven.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add mushrooms and soup. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add broccoli last.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter gradually.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Gradually add to egg mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts. Turn into greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inches).
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour apples into buttered baking dish.
Combine Bisquick, sugar and egg.
Mix and spread over apples.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour oil over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: white pizza with shrimp and spinach
directions: Preheat oven according to pizza dough package.
Cut shrimp into bite-size pieces.
Add onion, mushrooms, spinach (squeeze out all water), garlic, onion powder and pepper.
Sprinkle over mixture to moisten.
Spray bottom of baking sheet only with Pam. Spread dough in pan evenly.
Top with shrimp mixture and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until crust is crispy and cheese bubbles.
Makes 12 slices.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except mayonnaise.
Add the mayonnaise (may add more, if desired).

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Pour marinara sauce into saucepan; heat.
Spoon 1 cup of sauce into the bottom of a large roasting pan or 1/2 cup into each of two 2-quart baking dishes.
Reserve remaining sauce; keep warm.
Cook spinach as directed on package; drain and mix with Ricotta cheese, shredded Mozzarella cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese in large bowl.
Using a teaspoon, fill each shell with cheese mixture.
Arrange shells in single layer on sauce in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with reserved hot sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in margarine.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift flour, soda, ginger and cinnamon together.
Stir into creamed ingredients.
Mix into a ball and chill 15 minutes.
Form small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese bread
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in water.
Crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add well beaten egg, grated cheese and flour. Knead dough quickly and lightly until smooth and elastic.
Shape into loaf and place in greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from drafts, for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and beans over rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; add salsa.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: golden pitcher punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Add fruit juices and chill.
Pour into large pitcher and add ginger ale at serving time.
Pour over ice cubes in glasses. Makes 8 servings.

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: Heat oil (2-inches) in fryer to 375°.
Beat 1 cup baking mix, milk and egg with beater until smooth.
Coat cheese cubes lightly with baking mix.
Insert a wooden toothpick in each cheese cube. Dip in batter, covering cheese completely.
Fry several cubes at a time, turning carefully, until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 45 appetizers.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oil or margarine, egg, Sugar Twin, vanilla, salt and milk.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon and baking powder. Combine all ingredients, except oats and raisins.
Add oats and raisins; mix well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: texas garden dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except avocados.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Best if made the night before.
The flavors have time to blend.
Add avocados just before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cottage cheese horns
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours. Remove from refrigerator and divide in half.
Roll 1/2 mixture out like pie crust.
Cut in triangles.
Roll triangles up starting a big end to little end.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: puppy chow
directions: In microwave safe bowl melt chocolate chips for 1 minute. Stir, then heat an additional 30 seconds until melted.
Stir in peanut butter and peanuts.
Gently stir in cereal until well coated.
Put Confectioners sugar in 2 gallon zip lock plastic bag. Add cereal and close bag.
Toss gently until well coated.
Store in storage bag in refrigerator.
Yields 8 cups.

title: onion potato casserole
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes 1/4 inch thick. Do not peel. Rinse sliced potatoes in cold water and drain on paper towel, arrange in buttered 13 X 9 pan. Set aside. Combine butter, water, and onion soup mix in a saucepan, bring to a boil. Pour over potatoes. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve as a dip or as a topping for Mexican foods, sandwiches and snacks.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Heat beef paste and water.
Add vegetables.
When vegetables are about done, add potatoes.
(Soak in water or if you put in dry, add extra liquid.)
Simmer until done.
Makes 3 gallons for soup.

title: mom's steak and gravy
directions: Flour the steak. Brown in heavy pan for use in oven. After steak is browned, fill pan with water above steak. When water boils, sprinkle flour into boiling water until thickened for gravy. Steak is done when tender.

title: italian rice and chicken shrimp
directions: Marinate chicken and shrimp in Italian dressing overnight. Cook chicken breasts for 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Remove breasts; combine rice, dressing and water in bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken on top of rice and shrimp on top of chicken.
Bake another 25 minutes on 325°.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add chicken broth, carrots, potatoes, green beans, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve hot with saltine crackers.

title: chocolate ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Add melted butter; blend.
Pat into 9 x 13 pan, reserving some of the mixture for the top.
Freeze.
Soften ice cream. spoon onto crust.
Freeze.
Heat sugar, milk and chocolate in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Bring slowly to boil until thickened; cool.
Spoon over ice cream.
Freeze.
Spread whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining cookies on top. Freeze.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Blend well.
Bake in 9 x 14-inch greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: juicy barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in roasting dish, add remaining ingredients that have been mixed together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover the last 20 minutes.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers in length or round circles.
Salt, pepper and roll in flour. Fry in butter until tender and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine mayonnaise, mushroom soup, cheese, eggs, salt and onion.
Mix with broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour until bubbly at 350°.

title: hot salsa(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in blender for 40 seconds. Add crushed pepper, depending on how hot you like it.

title: baked steak
directions: Place steak on broiler pan.
Season; put sliced onions on the top, then the rounds of green pepper.
Pour the chili sauce over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 3/4 to 1 hour for a rare steak.

title: meatballs supreme
directions: Meatballs:
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, slightly beaten eggs and onion mix; stir completely together, then form meatballs.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Blend the Crisco until coarse and grainy.
Using a fork, stir in buttermilk. Do not overmix.
Put on a floured board and knead a few times. Roll out the dough about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter or glass.
Melt 1 tablespoon Crisco in a heavy black iron pan and place the biscuits in it; turn once in oil.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake at 450°.

title: b~b~q meat balls
directions: Mix all together except 1/4 cup Rice Krispies.
Set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag and shake beef strips a few a time to coat.
Heat the butter in a skillet; add meat and onion and brown well.
Prepare 2 cups of broth using the cubes.
Add to meat slowly and simmer 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms. Blend together the sour cream, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce.
Remove the pan from heat and add this mixture very slowly. Return to heat and cook over low heat, keeping mixture moving with a spoon, for about 5 minutes
until thoroughly heated; do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce made with love(yield: 2 quarts or more - plenty to freeze.)
directions: Add Garlic at your own risk...it is forbidden in our house!

title: fruit salad
directions: Dice oranges, apple and bananas.

title: puppy chow
directions: Microwave chocolate pieces and peanut butter until melted, approximately 2 minutes.
Mix together with cereal.
Pour the sugar on mixture and shake until coated.

title: chocolate mousse(makes 8 servings)
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium-low heat, melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into large bowl; cool to room temperature about 1 1/2 hours.
Beat until smooth. In large mixer bowl, beat cream until stiff; fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon mousse into dessert dishes.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix 1/4 cup mayonnaise, mustard and seasoned salt in saucepan. Add drained, cubed potatoes.
Heat, mixing gently.
Remove from heat. Add remaining mayonnaise, onion, celery, coarsely cut eggs, parsley and relish.
Mix lightly.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Mound potato salad in center of a lettuce lined serving dish.

title: jelly roll
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks and vanilla at high speed for 5 minutes, or until thick and lemon color.
Gradually add the 1/3 cup sugar, beating until sugar dissolves.
Thoroughly wash beaters.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites at medium speed until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold yolk mixture into whites.
Sprinkle flour mixture over egg mixture; fold in gently until blended.
Spread batter evenly into pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: peach cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, eggs and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan. Cover entire surface with fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Squirt with lemon juice.
Sprinkle with flour and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing.
Serve with ice cream.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Beat eggs with mixer thoroughly. Add grated cheese and mix well. Pour mixture into double boiler.
Add salt to taste.
Cook and stir over hot water until all is blended together.
Pour back into mixer bowl and add cut pimentos.
Start mixer and slowly add salad dressing, pickle juice and sugar.
After well mixed, store in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple and cherries in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dump cake mix on top of these.
Cut pieces of butter all over the top of this and sprinkle pecans on top.
Cook at 350° until golden.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 4 1/2 minutes or until hard.
Take shell off egg; split into halves.
Take out yellow and put in a bowl.
Add relish, mustard and mayonnaise.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Mix Accent, seasoned salt, lemon juice and Wesson oil.
Add to vermicelli and cover to marinate overnight, turning occasionally. Add next day the celery, pepper, onions, olives, pimentos and mayonnaise.
Sometimes I decorate the top with strips of pimento and green stuffed olives.

title: reese's easies
directions: Required:
miniature muffin tins and paper liners.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, cream of celery soup and peas and carrots; put in buttered Pyrex or Corning dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and margarine; pour over first mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili con cashews
directions: Saute garlic and vegetables (except tomatoes) in oil.
Add nuts, beans, tomatoes, seasonings and raisins.
Simmer for 2 hours in covered pot or in slow cooker.
Serve over cornbread or pasta, or with fresh bread or rolls.

title: hearty spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon slices until crisp; remove from skillet. Brown sesame seeds in hot bacon fat. Remove from the skillet. Drain and cool them. Add Parmesan cheese to seeds and mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Put rice in first in an oven casserole dish, then broccoli, soup, cheese and butter. Stir.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: my friend valerie's mom's shoestring potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place on a nonstick or greased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients well until creamy.
Blend remaining ingredients with first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Don't overbake.
Let cool completely.

title: red hot cinnamon cider
directions: In medium saucepan, combine apple cider and candies; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or until candies are dissolved.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: 24-hour vegetable salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, place 3 cups of the lettuce, salt and pepper to taste.
Layer eggs atop lettuce in bowl, standing some eggs on edge.
Sprinkle with salt.
Layer in order the peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise on top. Cover; let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: mochi rice stuffing
directions: Wash rice; drain.
Add water and soak for at least 1 hour. Cook rice in rice cooker.
Remove stems from mushrooms; chop caps. Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain excess oil.
Remove from heat.
Stir onions, green onions, char siu and mushrooms into mixture.
Cook until onions are clear.
Add remaining ingredients including cooked rice.
Mix gently and fry on medium heat.
Will be like fried rice, except a little stickier.

title: very good luncheon
directions: Mix and fill hamburger buns. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix sausage, bisquick, cheese and chilies together. Form egg shape around jalapenos; roll in `Shake & Bake'. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: divinity
directions: Slowly bring sugar, water, syrup and salt to a boil.
Cook to hard-ball stage.
Pour mixture over stiffly beaten egg whites; beat until it starts to thicken.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to drop a small amount at a time onto waxed paper. Cool.
Yields 36 pieces of candy.

title: sauerkraut topping for brats
directions: Drain sauerkraut very, very well.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling point.
Place sauerkraut in large container.
Add celery and onion.
Pour vinegar mixture over sauerkraut.
Cover and refrigerate a few days before serving.
Will cover 60 to 80 Brats.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut each package of cheese into 6 sections.
Fry tortillas lightly in oil, just until limp.
Place 1 section of cheese, along with a sprinkle of chicken, in each tortilla.
Roll and place in baking dish.
(This dish can be made ahead at this point and frozen.)

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Press crust in pan.
Whip until soupy cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust and let stand in refrigerator, about 15 minutes.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix all ingredients together but do not beat.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool or serve warm.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together, then add lemonade and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: citric acid punch
directions: Mix hot water and citric acid together 24 hours in advance. Then add other ingredients when ready to serve.
Will serve 60.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Wash zucchini well; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices. Combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Toss zucchini in mixture.
Slowly heat oil in large skillet.
Saute zucchini until golden brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large
mixing
bowl,
drain
juices of peaches and pears. Mix in 1/2
package of pudding mix and 1 tablespoon of instant Tang. Add
peaches,
sliced pears and drained cherries to mixture. Refrigerate.
Just
before
serving,
add	sliced bananas.

title: southwest-spiced roasted pork tenderloin
directions: In a small bowl, stir together paprika, salt, brown sugar, sugar, chili powder, ground cumin and black pepper until thoroughly blended. Makes 1/4 cup.

title: raisin torts
directions: Roll pastry out thin into 12 (4-inch) rounds. Fit each round into a muffin pan or cups.
Evenly divide raisins among pastry shells.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, oleo, egg, vanilla and salt.
Pour over raisins until 2/3 full.
Bake on lowest rack of preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Loosen edge and remove from pan.
Serves 12.

title: "mexican" casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Layer ingredients in casserole dish, beginning with corn chips, then beef and chili.
Repeat these layers 3 times. Pour 1/2 chili can of water over top (a little less if using an electric oven).
Add cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: favorite punch
directions: Mix
well and freeze.
Set out of freezer approximately two hours
before serving time.
Then add 28 ounces ginger ale or you may use Sprite or 7-Up.
Serves approximately 30.

title: mom's beef brisket
directions: Allow 1/2 pound of brisket per person.
Sprinkle generously with liquid smoke, tenderizer, salt and pepper.
Let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Place on foil and sprinkle both sides liberally with celery salt, paprika, nutmeg, garlic salt, onion salt and brown sugar.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Loosen foil slightly and bake 6 hours at 200°.

title: yankee pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done, but still firm.
Do not overcook. Rinse well until all of excess starch is rinsed off.
Drain very well.
Put into a large mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except cheeses.
Make sure ingredients are diced or chopped fine.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, peanut butter and sifted dry ingredients, alternate with milk.
Roll in balls and press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on Reynolds Wrap.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles. Set on paper towels to drain juice. Combine salt, red pepper onion powder stir. Add club soda and 2 tablespoons pickle juice. Your batter will be lumpy. Dip pickles into batter. Fry pickles until golden brown.

title: daddy's favorite applesauce cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, shortening and applesauce.
Beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan; cover and cook until tender.
Melt butter in Dutch oven or large pot over low heat; add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk gradually and cook until thick and bubbly.
Gradually stir in vegetable mixture, soy sauce, cheese and chicken.
Cook until cheese melts and mixture is well heated.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Chop onion and fry until tender.
Add onion, 1 beaten egg and cream cheese to mashed potatoes; add salt and pepper.
Put in a casserole.
Half hour before serving, bake in 350° oven.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour, powdered milk, baking powder and salt in a 4-quart storage container.
Blend/cut in shortening using a pastry blender or electric mixer until fine crumbs are obtained.
Store in tightly covered container.

Keep refrigerated for up to 3 months. Makes about 7 cups of biscuit mix and it can be used in recipes that call for commercial biscuit mix such as dumplings, pie crust, sugar cookies and any baking mix recipe.

title: stacy's peanut butter chews
directions: Place corn flakes in very large mixing bowl.
Combine sugar and Karo syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour cooked mixture over corn flakes. Stir to mix thoroughly.
Spoon individual cookies onto wax paper. Let cool for a few minutes and enjoy.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chicken broccoli curry
directions: In 10 x 10-inch casserole, layer chicken, broccoli and sauce made by combining remaining ingredients.
Repeat layer of chicken, broccoli and sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's papaya pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with fruit and cover with sugar, mixed with the tapioca.
Sprinkle lime juice over top with a little of the grated rind for delicious flavor.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat eggs with fork and add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Frost if desired.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Put
apricots
and
coconut through food grinder twice. Mix in	powdered
sugar,
nuts, orange rind and juices.
Form into small
balls
and roll in granulated sugar.
Dry several hours before storing in airtight containers.

title: frozen fruit pie
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice. Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups liquid. Put liquid, Jell-O, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup lemon juice in a saucepan. Bring to a boil while stirring. When dissolved, add pie filling, crushed pineapple, bananas and pecans. Cool. Pour into pie shells; refrigerate. Serve with Cool Whip. May be frozen. Thaw a few minutes before serving.

title: sara newberry's christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour, anise seed, baking powder and salt together.
Add shortening; mix well.
Add sugar, eggs and milk; beat well. Gradually add and blend in flour.
Chill.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage while Velveeta is melting in a crock-pot.
Mix everything together and let it heat.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash artichokes; blend in other ingredients. Sprinkle with more cheese; heat in oven until bubbly.
Serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Drain and chop peel.
Cream butter and sugar, add brandy and peel, mix well.

title: rich's pecan pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil; remove from the stove and cool completely.

title: make your own butter
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon whipping cream in a baby food jar.
Shake. Shake until solid butter forms.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes 1/8-inch.
Combine rest and brush over potatoes. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture. Brown meat in shortening.
Add water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover, simmer 2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells by package directions, drain, rinse well and set aside.
Combine chopped crab, chopped broccoli, Old Bay and 1 cup Mozzarella and mix well.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and mix well.

title: tommy's cole slaw
directions: Cook vinegar, oil, celery seed, mustard and salt to a boil. Pour over all.
Seal and set overnight.
Do not stir until ready to serve.

title: bonnie butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan or two 9-inch round layer pans.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat on high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt, alternately with milk on low speed. Add grated orange zest.
Bake until toothpick in center comes out clean, oblong 45 to 50 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Frost if desired.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Cook complete package of frozen mixed vegetables in 5 cups chicken broth and 2 tablespoons chopped onion (broth can be canned or made from bouillon cubes) for 5 minutes.
Thicken with flour mixed with 1 cup milk.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour half of mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with layer of chicken and then add remaining vegetable mixture. Prepare biscuit mix; pour on top.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes or until biscuit dough is golden brown.

title: seven layer jello
directions: To each package of jello, add 1 package Knox gelatine and 1 cup boiling water.

title: real chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar and milk in saucepan. Bring to a full boil then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vinegar, cornmeal and eggs.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 minutes.

title: low carb chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, juice, butter, and cheese; warm on stove. Combine chicken, soup mix, and broccoli in casserole dish. Top with bacon. Cook for 30 minutes. Top with other cup of cheese. Cook for 5- 10 minutes. Serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare taco seasoning as directions on package, then cool in fridge.

Mix together lettuce, tomatoes, onion and Cheddar cheese. Mix together taco seasoning mix and mixture of lettuce, tomatoes, onion and Cheddar cheese no sooner than 1 hour prior to serving. Then add Thousand Island dressing and nacho chips immediately before serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner as directed.
Saute mushrooms (can be fresh) and onions in margarine.
Combine all ingredients; mix well and place in greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish (or 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook your potatoes in their skins.
Mix and cook like a gravy everything but the bacon; cook until thickened.
Pour over the sliced potatoes.
Add chopped up bacon.

title: bacon baked beans
directions: Place bacon in a 2-quart casserole or a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High (100%) for 4 to 5 minutes or until crispy.
Remove bacon.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.

title: peachy bug(for children)
directions: Put peach half on lettuce leaf.
Make eyes on peach with cherry and also the mouth.
Stems you saved will be the antennae.

title: dropped raisin cookies
directions: Soak raisins in water for 5 minutes and boil 5 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Put cut-up chicken in a 6-8 quart saucepan.
Just cover with water to boil.
You can either boil the chicken until you can remove the meat off the bone, saving the broth, or you can add all the above ingredients to the whole cut-up chicken
and cook for about 1 hour.
After the chicken is cooked, remove the chicken and deboned it and return it to the pot and re-heat.
Serve hot over cooked medium egg noodles.

title: hearty chicken vegetable soup
directions: Place chicken, onion, celery, salt, basil and pepper in a 10 quart stock pot. Fill stock pot with water until ingredients are fully covered and bring to a boil. Let simmer for 1 and 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken from pot with slotted spoon and set aside for later. Add carrots, squash, zucchini, mushrooms, red pepper, tortellini, chicken soup base and uncooked noodles to stock pot and increase temperature to medium heat. While noodles and vegetables are cooking, tear chicken apart from bones. Cut up into pieces and add to soup in stock pot. Be sure to add additional water if ingredients are not fully covered. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for about 10 minutes or just until noodles are cooked.

title: cherry-pineapple coconut cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix pie filling and pineapple.
Mix together coconut and nuts and sprinkle over mixture.
Sprinkle cake mix over all.
Melt oleo and pour over cake mix.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: san diego shrimp salad
directions: Toast almonds about 4 to 6 minutes; set aside.
Combine shrimp, 1 pound grapes, celery, 1/4 cup of the toasted almonds, water chestnuts and pineapple in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, curry powder, marmalade, honey, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, cardamom, both mustards, dill weed, basil, garlic and lime juice in a blender.
Process at high speed 30 seconds.
Add remaining grapes and 1/4 cup almonds; process 20 seconds.
Add oil and salt and process until smooth.
Makes about 3 cups.
Toss with shrimp mixture and arrange on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine juices, 1/2 c. sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and remaining sugar, food coloring.
Pour over cherries in pastry lined pie pan.
Put a top crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If not sweet enough, sweeten to taste.

title: swiss potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil with bouillon in water until tender.
Layer with butter and Swiss cheese. Bake at 350° until hot.
Enjoy!

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat until light and frothy. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes.

title: never fail roast beef
directions: Lay roast on heavy foil in a pan.
On top of roast, add the ingredients in the order given.
Seal foil well.
Bake 1 hour for each pound of meat at 350°.

title: saucy fudge pudding
directions: Sprinkle over cake batter.
Over this, pour 2 1/2 cups hot water (do not stir).
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325° until cake pulls away from sides.

title: three bean salad
directions: In a small saucepan, bring to a boil the vinegar and sugar. Then add the oil and return to a boil.
Next, pour dressing over drained beans and chopped onions.
Put in airtight container and chil for at least 1 hour.
Can be kept for weeks.

title: coconut dream bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix next 7 ingredients.
Carefully spoon over baked crust.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on box; cool.
Add rest of ingredients and toss with salad dressing.
I usually add a large tablespoon of Hellmann's mayonnaise to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: In large bowl combine cabbage, onions and water chestnuts. Just before serving add the dry Ramen noodles, broken into small pieces and almonds.
Then pour dressing over it, made from sugar, vinegar, seasoning from noodle packages, oil, salt and pepper.

title: johnny marsietti(noodle casserole)
directions: Brown meat, onions, celery and bell pepper.
Drain.
Cook noodles while meat mixture is browning.
Drain noodles.
Add meat mixture to noodles.
Mix well.
Add tomato soup and tomato paste. Mix well.
Add olives and mushrooms and mix well.
Add one cup of the cheese and mix gently but thoroughly.
Pour into an oblong baking dish or pan (at least 9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and top is light brown.
Serve with green salad and garlic bread for a great meal.
(This recipe can be easily doubled or tripled, depending on the crowd you're serving.)

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 300 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Prepare dough as directed.
Spread Ragu evenly over dough surface.
Simmer ground beef until browned.
Sprinkle beef onto pizza.
Sprinkle mushrooms evenly.
Place pepperoni onto pizza as desired.
Sprinkle Cheddar and Mozzarella on top.
Place in oven preheated to 450° for 15 minutes.
Remove.
Cut into desired slices with kitchen scissors.
Serve hot.
Enjoy!
Serves 5.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix corn, butter, peppers, salt and onion rings in heavy saucepan.
Cook, covered, 7 minutes on medium heat.
Stir several times with spoon.
Add tomatoes and oregano.
Cook, uncovered, until tomatoes are done.

title: fajita fettuccine
directions: Sprinkle fajita seasoning on chicken breasts.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken and cook 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until done.
Remove chicken from skillet and let cool.
Cut into thin strips.
Add onion and pepper strips to skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until crisp-tender.
Stir in Alfredo Sauce.
Add chicken and fettuccine.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle with cilantro and serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: potato leek soup(vichyssoise)
directions: In a large soup pot, melt butter and saute leeks until limp 3-5 minutes.
Add potatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer until the potatoes are tender.
Cool slightly.
Puree in a blender or food processor until mixture is smooth.
Return to pot add heavy cream. Season to taste.
Chill the soup well or may be served hot.

title: walnut white fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk and sugar in medium heavy saucepan.

Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 4 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, morsels, walnuts and vanilla. Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted. Pour into foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Chill
until firm. Remove foil before cutting into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: garlic bread sticks
directions: Cut buns into fourths lengthways.
Melt butter, salt and garlic powder in medium skillet.
Roll buns in mixture, taking care not to leave too long to prevent sogginess.
Place buttered buns on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
They should crisp, not hard.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni following package directions; drain.
In a bowl, mix beaten eggs, milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over macaroni; add cheese (cut in small cubes).
Stir to blend.
Cook in a shallow baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: ham-cheese crackers
directions: Mix deviled ham, wine and mustard.
Spread on crackers. Sprinkle with grated sharp cheese.
Broil until bubbly.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature for 1 hour.
Chop dried beef very fine.
Chop green onions (include stems) very fine.
Combine all ingredients and shape into a ball.
Serve with favorite cracker.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: The following recipe is made with an electric blender, because it is so quick.
If you do not have one, gradually blend the eggs into the flour, beat in the liquid by spoonfuls, then the butter and strain the batter to get rid of any possible lumps.
Crepe batter should be made at least 2 hours before it is to be used; this allows the flour particles to expand in the liquid and insures a tender, light, thin crepe.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Add beaten eggs to sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Dot with butter.
Pour over rhubarb and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Makes a browned crust on top.

title: spring chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces (cubes).
Place chicken in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish; place cheese on top, then mixture of soup and water, poured onto cheese slices. Melt margarine; add stuffing until coated.
Layer stuffing mixture over entire baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of large brown paper grocery bag with Pam.
Pour popped popcorn into bag.
In a microwave-safe bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Stir in soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn in bag and close bag by folding down top. Shake bag.

title: melt in your mouth shark kabobs
directions: Dice shark, peppers, onion and red potato.
Marinate shark in teriyaki barbecue sauce.
Alternate veggies and shark on kabob sticks.
Baste entire kabob several times and grill.
Continue to baste as needed.
They are done when shark is flaky and veggies are semi-tender.
Serves 3.

title: pork teriyaki
directions: Prepare outdoor grill for cooking and preheat broiler.
Cut tenderloin lengthwise in half; don't cut all the way through.
Open and spread flat.
In small saucepan, over medium heat, combine lemon juice, honey, soy sauce, bouillon and ginger.
Heat until blended.
Place tenderloin on grill or broiler pan.
Grill or broil tenderloin, 15 to 20 minutes or until cooked through, turning and basting frequently with soy mixture.
To serve, slice tenderloin thinly.
Accompany with potatoes and cole slaw.
Serves 5. Per Serving:
280 calories, 6 g fat.

title: cheese olive appetizers
directions: Combine cheese, bacon, chopped olives, mayonnaise and onions; mix well.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of cheese mixture on each slice of bread.
Top each with olive slice.
Broil
2 minutes or until cheese melts; serve hot.

title: baked beans with beef
directions: Saute onion in skillet.
(If using minced onion, put in beans, not skillet.)
Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.

Cut cheese into squares and place in a microwave safe dish. Microwave on high for 2 minutes. Add rotel and microwave at 2 minute intervals stirring after each one until cheese is melted. Stir in beef.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter in a heavy bottomed saucepan. Stir over low heat until cheese is soft and butter is melted and the mixture is thoroughly blended.
Add the powdered sugar and stir until well combined.
Add food coloring and extract.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Place on a sheet of wax paper.
Press with a fork to form a design on top.
Let stand, uncovered, about 4 hours (until firm and outside is dry but inside is creamy).

title: cinnamon `n' spice fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine the whipped topping, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve with fruit.

title: leftover ham casserole
directions: Drain lima and kidney beans.
Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes.
Put in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cubed cheese over potatoes, onions, pimento, parsley, paprika and garlic salt.
Melt margarine.
Add bread crumbs and pour over entire casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
(May be made ahead of time.)

title: orange salad
directions: In large bowl, put cottage cheese.
Pour packet of Jell-O in with cottage cheese and mix.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture. Drain oranges and slice into small pieces, then add to mixture. Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into a Pyrex dish.
Crushed pecans can be added on top (optional).
Chill before serving.

title: connie's punch
directions: Mix, cool and serve.
Use ice ring, if desired.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp are just opaque and pink, about 2 minutes.
Transfer to platter
and keep
warm.
Add garlic and red pepper flakes to skillet
and cook,
stirring,
30 seconds.
Add wine and heat until
reduces to 1 tablespoon.
Remove from heat and whisk in butter 1 piece at a time.
Return shrimp to skillet with green onions and parsley. Season
with
salt	and
pepper.
Toss to coat.
Serve over cooked linguine.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Combine juices and syrup. Before serving, add ginger ale.

title: dumplings - for top of stew
directions: Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes until springy to touch and no longer doughy.

title: crab-shrimp bake
directions: Place in 1-quart casserole.
Combine 1 cup soft bread crumbs. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon melted butter on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue beef(serves 12)
directions: Combine ingredients in order given in slow cooker, 3 1/2 to 5-quart crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 8 hours.

title: pasta with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Start heating the water for the vermicelli.
Add onion and garlic and saute in oil over medium heat until golden.
Add vermicelli to the boiling water and cook according to package directions.
Drain clam liquid into the onion mixture.
Stir in wine.
Simmer about 5 minutes over medium heat. Stir in clams, parsley, pepper and butter.
Pour clam sauce over the hot, cooked and drained vermicelli.
Serve immediately.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a punch bowl.
Add the strawberries.
Float the sherbet on top.

title: refrigerated yeast rolls
directions: Oil bowl.
Mix yeast and water.
Melt butter and milk together.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix 1/2 of the flour into the yeast, water, butter and milk.
Use electric mixer.
Use dough hook when you add the second half of flour (not really necessary however). Place in oiled bowl and cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Let rise 1 hour after making into rolls.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: potato soup with variety
directions: Add all ingredients except instant potatoes in pot. Cover with water 1 to 2-inches over vegetables. Boil for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add instant potatoes, 1/2 cup or more, to thicken.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, measure all ingredients.

With mixer on low speed, beat until blended, scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Shape dough in ball; wrap in plastic and refrigerate 2 hours or until dough is firm enough to handle (or freeze for 40 minutes). Take out of refrigerator and cut into 1/4-inch slices and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Crumble yeast into crock or jar with wide mouth and a cover. Never use a metal container.
Add sugar and water, mix until smooth.
Add flour and beat to a smooth batter.
Keep in a slightly warm place 24 to 30 hours, when it should be sour and ready to use.

title: quick meal
directions: Cook at 350° until vegetables are tender and hamburger is cooked.
Add cheese; bake until cheese is melted.
May add fresh mushrooms.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Dissolve sugar and jello.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit and set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk; stir in jello and mix.
Add nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip.

title: ruth's chocolate pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream
sugar and shortening together well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. In another large bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa. Add dry mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto a cake rack.
This is not a "hurry up" cake.
You must beat the sugar mixture and each egg until mixture lightens.
This is very important!!

title: sweet yeast dough rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water; scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour; mix well. Add softened yeast and eggs; beat well.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead until satiny.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk. Punch down and shape into rolls or coffee cake.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sandra's chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, grape halves, apple, nuts and celery. Mix together sour cream and mayonnaise.
Toss well to coat.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: homemade hot fudge cake
directions: Toast slices of pound cake in oven on cookie sheet.
Add vanilla ice cream, Hot Fudge Sauce, whipped cream and cherries. It's delicious!

title: fried frog legs
directions: Skin frog legs and place into boiling water to which you have added salt and lemon juice.
Boil for about 2 minutes.
Remove from water and wipe dry.
Beat eggs lightly and dip legs in it, then roll them into cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown or until done.
This should be 3 to 5 minutes, depending on size of legs.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin slices.
Combine chicken and 1 tablespoon soy sauce in small bowl; let stand 30 minutes.

title: collard greens and ham hocks
directions: Combine ham hocks, water and onion in large pot.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours or until tender.
Wash greens well.
Remove ham hocks from liquid.
Chop ham and discard bone.
Add ham, greens and pepper to liquid.
Cover and cook slowly 30 to 45 minutes. Season with salt.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together flour, salt and spices; set aside.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add this to the flour mixture and fold in chopped prunes and nuts.
Bake at 350° until set in the middle, about 1 hour.
Bake in a tube pan or in two loaf pans.

title: fresh vegetable medley
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine in a large skillet 2 minutes.
Add frozen okra, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat 4 minutes, stirring gently.
Add corn and cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato and squash to skillet; continue to cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove garlic before serving.
Yields 8 servings.
Serving size:
1/2 cup. (Low cholesterol recipe.)

title: venison
directions: Cut meat in small pieces. Chop.
Salt and pepper. Cook in a frying pan in hot oil until brown.
Place in slow cooker on medium heat.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Stack tortillas on top of each other and cut into eighths.
Spread tortillas on baking sheet and spray with oil lightly.

Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until just beginning to turn brown. May vary recipe by sprinkling chips with garlic powder, onion powder, chili powder, Parmesan cheese, paprika or other seasonings before baking.

title: manicotti
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add Italian seasoning, oregano, salt, sugar, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer sauce.

title: cocoa-almond brownies (wheat-free, no sugar)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Combine cocoa, Splenda and flours stirred to evenly distribute. Combine melted butter with beaten eggs; stir in vanilla and almond extracts.
Add flour mixture and stir until well-combined.
Stir in almonds, if using.
Spread in pan and bake in center of oven for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Divide corn into 2 ungreased pans.
Mix all ingredients, except soda.
Cook and stir constantly until bubbly around the edges.
Continue cooking on medium heat 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over corn and mix well.
Cook 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, drain. Add everything else and simmer for a few minutes. Serve over buns or toasted bread.

title: rice pudding
directions: Grease crock-pot well.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours or automatic for 3 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add all ingredients in order. Shape into balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
These may be frozen in advance and baked when needed.

title: lucky if you get a bite
directions: Mix butter and flour; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press flat with no edges.
Brown as in pie crust.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; pour into crust.
Mix the pudding and milk; pour over cheese mixture.
Top with more Cool Whip and nuts.

title: cappuccino yogurt cafe
directions: Place frozen yogurt in 10 or 12-ounce coffee mug.
Add hot coffee slowly.
Top with dollop of whipped topping and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving with 110 calories per serving.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Remove several sheets of crackers and place them in the middle of a clean dish towel.
Fold the towel in half and use a rolling pin to crush the crackers into a fine crumb mixture.
Pour the crumb mixture into a medium bowl.
Add the sugar and mix well. Cream the butter into the mixture until the butter practically disappears.

title: burgundy beef cubes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ovenproof pan; cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions, drain.
In medium saucepan melt butter or margarine.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, onion and mustard.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Combine cheese sauce and macaroni, mix well. Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry onion until tender in oil.
Add pepper and hamburger meat. Cook until brown.
Drain and rinse to remove excess grease.
Put meat mixture, salt to taste, tomato sauce, Lawry's seasoning, chili powder, 3 shakes of Worcestershire and 1 can water in skillet.
Add mushrooms and olives if desired.
Bring to boil and let simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: chocolate dipped fruit
directions: Drain fruit on paper towels for several hours.
Melt confectioners coating.
Hold fruit by one end, and dip a portion into melted coating.
Let excess coating drip off fruit.
Place on a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Let dry.
If desired, drizzle with additional melted coating.
Serve fruit the same day it is dipped.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine caramels, half and half and butter in glass bowl or pie plate.
Heat on Medium (50%) power of microwave for 30 seconds.
Stir.
Continue on Medium power and stir every 30 seconds for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Serve warm Caramel Sauce over Oatmeal Pie with ice cream on top.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased pan.
Salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over top.
Sprinkle on parsley.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: banana-chocolate muffins
directions: In medium bowl, mix oats and milk. Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir in egg, oil, bananas, brown sugar and chocolate chips.
In a large bowl, mix flours, baking powder and salt. Stir mixtures together just to moisten well. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 18 muffins.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Mix; let stand 3 hours.
Stir to blend several times.
Then put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: nutty popcorn(child snack recipe)
directions: Combine popcorn, peanuts, oat cereal, marshmallows and raisins in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
The mixture can be stored in an airtight container until ready to serve.

title: french toast deluxe
directions: Mix syrup, eggs, milk and salt in shallow bowl. Dip bread into mixture; drain slightly.
Fry on both sides in hot, lightly greased pan.

title: french pistachio ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, add remaining ingredients, except nuts; beat well. Add nuts to freezer after freezing process has begun.
Freeze in a half gallon ice cream freezer.
Double recipe for gallon size freezer.

title: candy bar squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear; beat eggs with heavy cream.
Add ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Great with a salad.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour in 325° oven.
Cool 10 minutes.
Glaze with 1 cup confectioners sugar and juice and grated rind of lemon.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions slowly with butter and oil in a heavy, covered, 4-quart saucepan for 15 minutes.
Stir in salt and sugar; raise heat to moderate.
Cook, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes, stirring often, until onions are a deep golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour; stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add bouillon and boiling water; blend well.
Add wine; season to taste.
Simmer, partly covered, about 35 minutes longer.** Bring to boil.
Pour into ovenproof tureen.
Stir in slivered cheese and grated onion.
Float toast rounds on top of soup; spread grated cheese over toast.
Sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Set under broiler for a minute or two to brown top lightly.
Serve at once. Makes 8 servings.

title: swiss steak surprise
directions: Brown steak in
dressing.
Add
soup and 1/4 cup water. Simmer 2 hours.
Serve with noodles.

title: country chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan, combine broth and rice, heat to boiling over medium-high.
Reduce heat and cook on low for 15 minutes or until rice is done, stirring occasionally.
Add mixed vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat through; stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: fruitcake
directions: Mix
flour
and
sugar with diced fruit and nuts.
Beat eggs and
butter
with
flavoring.
Stir into fruit and flour mixture until
well
mixed.
Mix and bake in large brownie pan (9 x 13-inches)
at
400° for 10 minutes.
Stir very well and bake 10 minutes more.
Stir.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Stir and put into Pam sprayed 12 cup Bundt pan.
Refrigerate overnight. Turn out
and wrap
very
tightly.
Will keep for 2 months or more in refrigerator.
Can be frozen also.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken or hen until done in seasoned water.
Remove from broth.
Have White Lily sifted in large bowl or pan.
Make well in flour.
Beat egg(s) well, then add water and food coloring.
Pour into well in flour and knead until stiff.
Roll thin and cut in small pieces.
Drop into chicken broth which should be boiling rapidly.
(Lower heat while you are rolling dumplings, then turn heat up when you start adding dumplings.)
Cook until dumplings are tender (do not overcook).
Remove chicken from bone and add to dumplings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni, drain, add 1 can of sauce and mix.
Butter the bottom of casserole dish, pour a little milk on bottom.
Put a layer of macaroni mix, sprinkle with grated cheese, top with American cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers until macaroni is gone. Add remainder of milk almost to the top of the dish.
Then place in oven and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix cookies and margarine and spread with fork in a long glass cake pan.

title: ham rolls
directions: Lay ham, cheese and broccoli.
Roll each and place in baking dish.
Warm sauce of cream of celery soup and milk.
Pour over rolls.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: party style burritos
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until done.
Drain off grease.
Add roast, gravy and pinto beans.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add all spices, then cook for 10 more minutes.
Heat up flour tortillas. Add mixture and roll up.
Can add fresh tomatoes, cheese and lettuce.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix syrup, molasses and vinegar in pan.
Cook until mixture forms a brittle ball when dropped in cold water.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Stir into molasses mixture.
Add popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Salt and pepper.
Roll in flour. Brown in Crisco.
Put in deep pan, thighs on bottom and legs on top.
Add soup.
Spread around on chicken.
Put on lid and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar until sugar is thoroughly dissolved over medium heat.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Place in containers and freeze.
Also keeps well in refrigerator.

title: ranch chicken ball
directions: Cream together cream cheese, chicken breast chunks and salad dressing mix.
Refrigerate for several hours in a Cool Whip tub which has been lined with Saran Wrap.
After several hours (or overnight), turn out onto a plate and top with almonds.

title: broccoli pea casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as on package.
Drain.
Arrange 1 package on bottom of a greased 2-quart dish and cover with 1/2 can of peas. Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper, cheese, onion and eggs to make the sauce.
Pour half of the sauce over the broccoli and peas.
Then repeat the process again.
Sprinkle the crushed crackers over the top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: To microwave:
In a large bowl, thoroughly blend beef, 1/2 cup of soup, eggs, crumbs and Worcestershire.

title: creamy vanilla frosting
directions: Mix sugar and margarine. Stir in vanilla and milk. Beat until smooth and of spreading consistency. Frosts a 13 x 9 cake.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Roll chicken and debone.
Take cream cheese and add a little milk to thin down just a touch.
Mix chicken and drained mushrooms thoroughly.
In another bowl, melt oleo and add poppy seed.
Crush the crackers and mix together.
Take half or a little more to layer a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in chicken mixture.
Put the rest of the cracker mix on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stewed meat
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with undiluted soup.
Rinse can with about 1/4 cup water.
Season. Cover and bake in slow to moderate oven for 2 hours or until cooked (should break apart easily).
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine sugar, allspice, cloves, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cider in large saucepan.
Slowly bring to a boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve in mugs garnished with an orange wedge.

title: spring salad
directions: Prepare vegetables and fry bacon.
Toss the vegetables together.
Mix sugar, Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Add to vegetables and mix.
Add bacon pieces and salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: noodles con carne
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion, beans, and noodles; then add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Stir in flour and spice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Whip ingredients together.
Put in graham cracker crust; chill in refrigerator.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Lay out biscuits in two rows of five on a floured cookie sheet. Using a rolling pin, roll the biscuits into a flat, rectangular shape. Next, sprinkle ham, cheese and onion evenly over biscuits. Roll the ingredients into a long jelly roll. Slice into round pieces approximately 1/2-inch thick. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes. (Biscuits should be a light golden brown and cheese melted.) Serve warm.

title: soup and meat pie with potatoes
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie or cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Frost with mashed potatoes.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: stir-fried pork and sugar peas
directions: String in peas and cook in large pot of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
Chop onion.
Cut pork into 1/2-inch slices. Cut each slice into thin strips.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a wok or large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the remaining oil.
When hot, add the pork strips and cook, stirring, until browned, about 2 minutes.
Add ginger; cover and cook until meat is done, about 2 minutes.
Stir in red pepper flakes and peas; heat through.
Serve alone or over rice.

title: sherry chicken casserole
directions: Prepare chicken for frying except salt sparingly.
Put margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and heat in oven at 400° until melted.
Put chicken in butter and cook for 30 minutes, turning once.
Mix chicken soup, water, mushroom soup, cooking sherry and bouillon cubes in saucepan.
Simmer until well blended.
Pour over chicken that has been cooked.
Return to oven and cook at 325° for 1 hour, basting every 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: holiday spaghetti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon.
Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in hot drippings until onion is yellow.
Add ground chuck and cook until browned.
Add rest of ingredients and heat. Pour into well-greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated sharp cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve hot, garnished with crisp bacon and parsley.

title: turkey rolls with gravy
directions: Make Stove Top stuffing as directed on box.
Take pieces of turkey and add Stove Top on the turkey breast.
Roll each piece up and secure with a toothpick.
Pour gravy over turkey roll-ups in long baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick brownies
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer.
Spread in 13 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.
Extra good with scoop of ice cream on each serving.

title: kart wheels
directions: Mix flour, margarine, powdered sugar, baking powder and milk until dough forms.
If dough is dry, add a little more milk.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar. Add melted margarine and vanilla. Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 45 minutes at 375° or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: texas pralines
directions: Line a	large
cookie sheet with waxed paper.
In heavy saucepan combine sugar, buttermilk, butter and soda.
Stirring constantly, cook
on
low
heat
until
mixture boils, about 5 minutes.
Stirring	often,	continue cooking until candy thermometer reaches
or
a
small of mixture dropped in cold water forms
a
ball.
Remove
from heat; cool 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and
pecans.
Beat until mixture begins to lose gloss. Drop by spoonful on prepared cookie sheet.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Store in airtight container.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in garlic and butter.
Top with Provolone and Parmesan cheese.
Bake on a platter until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and dip vegetables.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry with paper towel.
Combine soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, pepper and garlic in large microwave-safe casserole with lid; add chicken pieces, skin side down.
Cover and microwave on High 10 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over; rearrange in dish.
Cover and microwave on High 13 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender, rearranging pieces once.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender at one time.
Count to 10 slowly.
Pour into a 10-inch Pyrex pan and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chili-cheese cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Combine sour cream, eggs and vegetable oil in medium bowl.
Stir well.
Add cornmeal mixture, cheese, corn and chilies.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: harvard beets
directions: Boil all ingredients except beets for 5 minutes.
Toss fished sauce with beets.
Serve warm or cold.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Using a glass 9 x 13-inch dish, melt the butter in the microwave.
After the butter has melted, mix all the ingredients in the same dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: country meat pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pat meat into bottom and pinch flutings around the edges of a greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Mix other ingredients together with meat and cook until done.

title: ground beef dinner
directions: Layer vegetables, in order given, into slow cooker.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put beef on top of celery.
Mix tomato soup and water and pour into slow cooker.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: dream cheese cake
directions: Combine 1 cup graham cracker crumbs with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate. Set aside remaining 1/4 cup of graham cracker crumbs.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate eggs, keeping egg yolks whole.
Set yolks aside. Add 1 teaspoon cream of tartar to egg whites, beat until foamy; set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add 3 cups sugar while beating.
Add baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Add vanilla; mix.
Add egg yolks one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each one.
Add egg whites; mix thoroughly. Pour mixture into refrigerated spring-form pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Increase to 350° until cake is firm.
Turn oven off and crack door.
Let cake cool in oven.
When cool, undo spring-form pan and serve plain or with topping.

title: grandma brock's doughnuts
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out and cut in shapes; then deep fry.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Pour 1/2 batter into greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 sugar mixture and cut into batter.
Repeat once.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer for desired brown color.
Cool before removing from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yield:
1 Bundt pan cake.

title: mock oysters rockefeller
directions: Cook
broccoli	according to package directions; drain. In a medium
saucepan, melt butter; add onion and saute until soft. Add soup, mushrooms, broccoli and garlic cheese spread; mix well. Keep hot and allow cheese to melt.	Add almonds and stir well.
At serving time, bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon into chafing dish; serve hot.
Serves 25.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook hamburg and onions until done.
Put mixed hamburg, onions and corn in a casserole pan.
Put mashed potato on top.
Cook at 350° until top of potatoes turn light brown.

title: squash patties
directions: Be sure squash is exactly 3 level cups.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese and the onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth (on high speed in mixer for 1 minute).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just enough for cheese to melt.
Garnish with tomato slices if desired.
Makes 6 servings (405 calories per serving).

title: american flag cake
directions: Leave spaces for stars.

title: nifty nippy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: shrimp and green rice
directions: Cook shrimp; peel and devein.
Set aside.
Heat all other ingredients together.
Stir in shrimp; heat very slowly.

title: coco-not cookies
directions: Cream
together butter, sugar and coconut extract.
Add egg and
beat,	stir in biscuit mix and potato flakes.	Cover and chill
for about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into marble-sized
balls
and
place
about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: key lime pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks. Add condensed milk and beat until well blended.
Slowly add lime juice, mixing well (custard will thicken as you add lime juice).
Pour immediately into a baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 325° until meringue is browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower pepperidge style
directions: Cook cauliflower or broccoli as directed on package.
Make white sauce of 1 tablespoon butter, flour and milk.
Place vegetables and white sauce in buttered casserole.
Melt 2 3/4 tablespoons butter with water and blend with stuffing mix.
Place on top of vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diet drink
directions: Mix, cool and drink.

title: pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: In large skillet, heat oil on medium-high heat.
Saute garlic until golden.
Add chicken strips and saute until white and almost completely done.
Add broccoli and stir-fry until crisp-tender. Add tomatoes, basil, hot sauce, wine, chicken broth and margarine. Cook for 3 minutes until heated through.
Toss cooked pasta with chicken mixture.
Serves 6.

title: one step lasagna(microwave)
directions: Brown and crumble meat; drain.
Mix spaghetti sauce, water and salt together; microwave, covered, 5 to 6 minutes on High until hot.
In a 7 x 12-inch glass baking dish, layer 1/3 sauce, 1/2 uncooked noodles and 1 cup cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tight with plastic wrap; microwave 30 to 35 minutes on High.
Turn dish once after 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Let sit in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Put in a large bowl and mix well.

title: peach wedding ring salad
directions: Drain peaches well.
Overlap slices in 1 1/2-quart ring mold. Outline ring with quartered cherries.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add ginger ale.
Spoon a little gelatin into mold around fruit.
Chill.
Chill remaining gelatin until thickened.
Beat until fluffy with rotary beater.
Chop remaining peaches; fold into gelatin with nuts.
Turn into mold over clear layer. Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.
Serve with mayo (optional). Can also be molded in oblong Pyrex dish. Cut into squares and use spatula to remove and turn over to see peaches and cherries.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake one pie crust.
Bring to a boil, sugar, salt and water. Stir in the jello, cornstarch and cold water in hot mixture until it thickens.
Cool.
Pour some of the mixture in the bottom pie shell and then place the strawberries.
Add remainder.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins. Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in raisins.

title: tamale beef tangle
directions: Brown beef; add onions and cook until browned.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake in 325° to 350° oven 35 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: stromboli
directions: Allow loaf
of	bread to thaw and roll into a rectangle shape about
1/4-inch
thick.
Layer
cheese
and
meat, then spread drained
salad
pepper
on	top.
Roll
bread up like a jelly roll.
Brush beaten egg whites on top of loaf.
Sprinkle seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower-broccoli toss
directions: Prepare cauliflower and broccoli by cutting into bite-size. Add green onions.
Toss.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: camper's dish
directions: Brown hamburg; saute onion and mix together.
When hamburg is done, add cans of corn and kidney beans.
Cook until everything is hot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with biscuits.

title: cider - hot and spicy
directions: Heat until hearts are melted. Serve hot.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together and pour into crust. Bake at 275° for 80 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water, sugar and Sweet 'N Low in a gallon jar. Shake this up until all is mixed. Add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
If time is permitting, place this in freezer all day to let chill. If not, add ice when serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything together and put in a buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inches). You can add cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.
Save 1 cup and mix with pudding and Tang.
Add fruit and mix all together.
Chill until serving.

title: pecan logs
directions: Work with fingers until mealy.
Roll into 6 or 7 logs.
Put in wax paper or freezer for 2 to 3 days.

title: country fried steaks
directions: Cut steaks from
boneless
beef roast in 1/2-inch thick steaks.

title: caramelized apples
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet, medium heat.
Add apples and cook.
Stir until golden, about 8 to 12 minutes.
Stir in cider, lemon juice and cinnamon and bring to a boil.
Makes 2 cups.
Good with pancakes, waffles or with a main dish.

title: oatmeal fruit bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix and oats. Add butter and egg and stir until crumbly. Put 1/2 mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Press down lightly. Spread filling over mixture in pan. Top with remaining mixture. Press down lightly. Bake at 375° for 22 to 26 minutes. Cool before cutting in squares.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients except chicken, butter, salt and pepper in baking dish or pan.
Dip chicken in melted butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with buttermilk, beating smoothly. Stir in jam, nuts and raisins.
Pour into four 9-inch layer pans, greased and lined with paper.
Bake in preheated 325° oven about 35 minutes.
Cool and spread Caramel Frosting between layers and on top of cake.
