title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 375° until rice is cooked.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, then mix in crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle a few crushed crackers on top of casserole. Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add whole kernel corn (drained), condensed cream of chicken soup, condensed cream of mushroom soup, dairy sour cream, chopped pimento, salt, monosodium glutamate and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in medium noodles, cooked and drained.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.

title: chocolate molokoo
directions: Sprinkle ladyfingers with Triple Sec or other orange liqueur; set aside remaining liqueur.
Let ladyfingers absorb on cookie sheet.

title: dad's kidney bean gumbo
directions: While boiling link sausage, put rice into a large skillet with melted butter and brown. Add 2 cups water, tomatoes, barbecue sauce and jalapenos.
Stir. Cover, bring to a boil, then simmer. When sausage is finished boiling, cut up and add to ingredients in skillet. Stir and continue to simmer (while stirring), approximately 60 minutes.
(If need more water, add a little water from the boiled sausage in saucepan.)
Serve when done!

title: king ranch style
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add soup and tomatoes; mix well. Season with garlic salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add chicken to mixture.
In casserole dish, alternate layer of chips, then put chicken mixture over the chips.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange steak in roaster or casserole large enough to hold them in a single layer (do not brown meat first).
Cut potatoes, carrots, onions and celery in large chunks and layer on top of meat (as much as desired).
Mix tomato sauce with water and sugar. Pour over meat and vegetables.
Salt and pepper.
Scatter tapioca on top.
Can add beef bouillon cubes for flavor if you like.
Seal roaster tightly in heavy foil.
Bake at 325° for at least 2 hours.
Do not open during recommended cooking time.
When foil is removed, meat will be brown with gravy.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and boil chicken.
When done, remove chicken from bone.
(May use boneless chicken.)
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish and top with steamed broccoli.
Pour 1 can of soup over broccoli. Top with cheeses and sprinkle Ritz crackers on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes (until cheese melts).

title: penne alla vodka
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in oil and butter for about 5 minutes.
Add prosciutto and vodka and cook over medium-low heat for 5 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes, basil, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Add half and half and cook 5 minutes longer.
Toss in cooked pasta and heat through for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Get Boone to make you loaf of rye bread.
Cut two pieces of the bread about 1/2 inch thick.
Then go over to the toaster and put them in it.
Toast to a light brown.
Take them out and butter them (will be hot).
Then take some ham and cheese or peanut butter and put them on.
Let them melt together.
Repeat if still hungry.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Coat a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with non-stick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl combine 3/4 cup sugar, butter, flour, milk, baking powder, and salt; mix well. Pour batter into the prepared baking dish.
In a medium bowl combine the blackberries and remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well and spoon over the batter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: microwave chicken and dumplings
directions: Put butter, onion, celery and garlic into 3-quart glass baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, until crisp-tender, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes at High; stir after 1 minute.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables and mix well.
Add chicken broth, sugar, salt, pepper, basil, bay leaf and parsley; stir.
Microwave, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes at High or until thickened; stir occasionally.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces; salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Put in ovenproof dish.
Add water; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: switchell
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shake well.
A real thirst quencher!

title: banana slush
directions: Boil 3 minutes and cool the 6 cups of water and sugar.
Mix orange juice, 12 ounces of water, frozen lemonade, 6 ounces water and pineapple juice.
Crush ripe bananas.
Semi freeze.
Add vodka, if desired . To use as a punch, add 3 quarts of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: orange iced cranberry cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, sour cream, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, leveling off.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Blend well. Gently stir in cranberries and nuts.
Do not overmix.
Drop by teaspoons, 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: baked herb fillets
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and salt. Dip fillet in egg white and place fillets, one at a time, in a bag with the herb mixture.
Make sure each fillet is coated. Remove and arrange fillets in a baking dish.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 15 minutes (until fish flakes easily) or in microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat 1-inch salted water to boiling. Add broccoli. Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Place in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook hen in pressure cooker for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pull chicken from
bone and dice.
Chop onions and celery.
Combine all ingredients
and put in the broth from the chicken.
Bring to boil and
lower
heat to simmer.
Cook 3 to 4 hours using a heavy pot. Serve over chow mein noodles and/or rice.

title: spanish rice
directions: Wash and dry rice.
Brown rice in hot oil.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, chili powder and tomatoes; mix well.
Add enough water to cover mixture.
Cover; let simmer until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: dorothy smith's cream pie
directions: Scald milk; heat, but not to boiling point.
In top of double boiler pan, mix flour and cornstarch with sugar.
Stir until dissolved into hot milk.
Beat egg yolks with a fork until fluffy. When mixture begins to get thick, take out approximately 1/4 cup of mixture and beat into egg yolks, then add eggs to pan of custard and cook until thick.
Take off stove and add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and serve, or stir once a day and keep for a week in refrigerator.

title: pecan chews
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in square baking pan, or spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Add ingredients together, except nuts, in order and stir just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crockpot chili
directions: Soak beans in a bowl overnight. In the morning, place beans in crockpot with remaining ingredients. Cook on low 7 to 8 hours. Serve with sour cream, cheddar cheese, olives and flour tortillas.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Saute onions in bacon fat. Combine in frypan the mustard, vinegar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, water and salt. Add onions. Simmer. After mixture cools, put in blender to chop onions even finer and to blend thoroughly. Pour over cut up wieners in crock-pot. Cook on low 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Sift powdered sugar and powdered milk; set aside.
Add syrup, water and vanilla to peanut butter mixture.
Stir in half of the dry ingredients.
Blend well. Add remaining dry ingredients.
Blend until very smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Turn into buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: sopaipillas(fried puffs)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add beaten eggs, butter and milk and as much flour as it will absorb.
Knead as for tortillas, only make balls the size of walnuts.
Press thin or roll with rolling pin as thinly as possible.
Fry on both sides in deep fat until a delicate golden brown.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift
together
flour,
sugar,
baking powder and salt. Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually beat 1/2
cup
sugar,
little at time.
Beat until stiff peak forms. In
a small bowl, combine egg yolk, water, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes, fold yolk mixture gently in beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice, reserved from can of crushed pineapple. Add orange jello; cool.
When cool, add Dream Whip or Cool Whip, pears and mayonnaise.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until browned.
Add peppers; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir cornstarch and soy sauce in small bowl.
Add soy sauce mixture, pineapple in juice, vinegar, sugar, ginger and garlic powder to skillet; bring to a boil.
Serve chicken mixture over hot rice.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Heat oil (not too hot); add seasonings.
Stir until fairly dissolved.
Pour over crackers in a large roaster.
Warm in 200° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Keep in airtight container.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Melt margarine and chips together; add milk and warm up.
Stir in the marshmallows and stir to combine, but don't overcook! Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan; sprinkle 1/2 of peanuts in bottom of pan.
Pour heated mixture over top; add rest of peanuts on top and cool in refrigerator.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove from broth and cook noodles in chicken stock.
Saute onion and bell pepper with oleo.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Bake in large casserole dish, covered with foil, until hot and bubbly.

title: minute rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes and stir twice.
Add cinnamon on top.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oats, vanilla, pecans, coconut and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine together until smooth. Add powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Spread on any two or three layer cake. Sprinkle with coconut flakes and pecans.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well. Spread dough into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to
30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle immediately with chips; let stand several minutes to melt.
Spread melted chocolate evenly over surface; sprinkle with pecans.
Cool; cut in bars. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: clairmont salad
directions: Combine vegetables and cover.
Blend other ingredients; shake well.
Pour over vegetables and marinate, uncovered, out of refrigerator for 2 hours.
Cover and refrigerate until used.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil brown sugar, Karo and salt for 5 minutes.
Add soda and butter.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread in baking pans and bake in oven at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip(teacher appreciation week)
directions: In medium bowl, mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Serve with cut up fruit.
Enjoy.

title: texas barbecue hot beef
directions: Bake at 300° for 3 hours in tight covered container or crock-pot.
Be sure it juices itself.
Add about 1 cup Heinz barbecue sauce and continue cooking until you know meat will flake when done.
Good on toasted 1/2 buns.

title: oysters in patty shells
directions: Combine butter and oysters in skillet; cook over low heat for 2 minutes. Add onion, garlic, parsley, celery and mushrooms; heat until celery is crisp-tender. Drain. Stir in seasonings and soup; cook just until thoroughly heated. Spoon into patty shells. Serve immediately. Yield: 12.

title: tuna boats
directions: Combine cheese, eggs, celery, green pepper, pickle, mayonnaise, and tuna until well blended.
Fill hot dog buns.
Wrap each bun in foil.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: crustless chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and then add the rest.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Place peaches and juice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: baked stuffed potatoes(mihshi batata)
directions: Peel and wash the potatoes.
Make a hole on one side of the potato and scoop out the pulp, leaving a shell 1 cm. thick.
Brown the potatoes lightly in hot oil; set aside.
Saute the pine nuts in Crisco until golden brown; remove from the pan and add the meat and onions to the saucepan, adding salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add the pine nuts to the meat and stuff the potatoes completely with the meat mixture.
Arrange the potatoes in an ovenproof dish.
Add water, 1 teaspoon salt and lemon juice.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with rice.

title: mini mushroom quiche
directions: Lightly grease muffin cups with butter or cooking spray. Roll pastry dough out to 1/16-inch thickness.
Cut six circles 5 1/2 to 6-inches in diameter.
Line each cup with a circle of dough, being careful not to stretch dough.
Trim and flute edges. Prick sides and bottom of each with a fork. Put in oven and bake on 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sundrop punch
directions: Mix chilled fruit juices and water in punch bowl.
Just before serving, add slightly softened sherbet and stir briefly.
Add chilled Sundrop and serve.
Serves 16.

title: elk stew
directions: Cut up elk into small bite size pieces.
This should take about a week.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over wood fire for 3 days at 450°.
This will serve 200 people.
If more are expected, the two jack rabbits may be added.
But do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: pickled okra
directions: Put okra pods, garlic and lots of dill weed (or dill seed) in each jar. Add 1 small hot pepper to each jar. Boil vinegar, water and pickling salt. Pour this boiled mixture over mixture in jars and seal with a 2 piece lid set. Process jars in boiling water bath for 15 minutes. Take out jars and tighten lids.

title: pecan crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam cooking spray.
Place crackers on pan.
Combine sugar and butter in a saucepan; simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add pecans.
Pour mixture over crackers. Spread with brush for even coat.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Separate and place on platter.

title: my favorite pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine first 6 ingredients; stir until well blended. Then stir in nuts. Pour into pastry-lined pan. Decorate top with pecan halves. Bake 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown and filling is set.

title: fish beer batter
directions: Mix all ingredients; add enough beer to batter as thin or thick as you like it.
Dip fish and drip off.
Deep fry.

title: little chocolate pots
directions: Pour milk into heavy saucepan; heat to boiling.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender or food processor; pour in hot milk.
Blend at low speed for 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour mixture into 6 custard cups.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cookies and cream pudding pie
directions: Place cookies on bottom and sides of pie plate.
Cookies should cover plate evenly.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of cold milk into bowl.
Add ice cream.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended. Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let pudding stand for 3 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, celery, eggs, olives, onions and dill pickle. Blend mayonnaise, chili sauce, horseradish and salt.
Add to shrimp mixture and toss lightly.
Chill.
Cut top off bread and remove insides, leaving a thick shell.
Combine cheese spread and margarine.
Spread inside of bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put shrimp salad in bread case and decorate.
Slice to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients using the milk and coffee.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter; add cheese, onions, sour cream and chicken soup. Add to hash brown potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered salad supreme
directions: In an 11 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer ingredients in the order given.
Refrigerate.
May be prepared up to 48 hours in advance.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in a 9 x 13 dish.
Cover with graham cracker crumbs.
Press down into butter.
Layer with sliced bananas.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and spread on top of bananas. Chill.
Cover with blueberry pie filling.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, ungreased.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: u.s.m.c. creamed beef on toast
directions: Brown meat.
Add butter and stir.
Add onion and cook until done.
Add flour and cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Stir until thickened. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on toasted bread slices.

title: bonnie's egg bake
directions: Remove crust from bread slices.
Generously butter sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.	Butter 8
slices
of
bread and place, buttered side, down.
Sprinkle ham over bread.
Sprinkle Cheddar (or place American slice) cheese over
ham	and
bread. Top with remaining 8 slices of bread, unbuttered.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over	bread.	Make
sure to
cover well.
Cover
and	refrigerate
overnight.
Combine Wheaties
and 1/4
cup
melted
butter.	Sprinkle
over	bread immediately before baking.
Bake at 350° for
one
hour, uncovered.
Freezes well for later use.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: In medium bowl mix black beans and 2 tablespoons salsa.
Mash with fork.
Stir until smooth.
On 12-inch platter spread bean mixture into 10-inch circle.
Top with sour cream; spread within 1/4 inch of edge of beans.
Top with 1 cup salsa, lettuce, cheese, olives, green onions and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mincemeat relish
directions: In medium bowl, stir mincemeat, pineapple and juice and remaining ingredients until mixed.
Cover and refrigerate, about 15 minutes before serving, or up to 1 week ahead.
Serve with poultry, baked ham, pork chops or on top of ice cream.

title: chocolate yogurt brandy
directions: Place ice cream, yogurt and brandy in blender until smooth. Pour into tall glass.
Garnish with whipped cream and a pinch of cocoa.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly about 10 to 20 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars.

title: apple butter(quick)
directions: Mix all together.
Let come to a boil.
Stir for 20 minutes. Can in jars.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt margarine in large container.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut, powdered sugar and vanilla; add peanut butter and mix well.
Roll into small nut-sized balls and lay on cookie sheet.
Dip in melted dipping chocolate.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed. Use the next ingredients in the middle and on top of layers. Bring sugar and milk to a boil. Add marshmallows, cook slowly until dissolved.	Cut heat off. Add coconut, vanilla and salt. Stir well. Spread onto cake layers.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and whip real good.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake for 1 hour.

title: kraut pork pinwheel
directions: Combine pork, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper; mix well. Place on a piece of aluminum foil and pat or roll out to approximately 10 x 7-inch rectangle.
Set aside.
Combine drained sauerkraut and onion; spread over the meat, then carefully roll up in jelly roll fashion.
Take the foil and seal in top and ends. Place on cookie tray.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven.
Slice and serve hot.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place the frozen dinner roll in the pan and sprinkle them with dry butterscotch pudding, brown sugar, slivered margarine and pecans. Place the pan in a cold oven and allow the rolls to remain there overnight. In the morning, bake the rolls at 350° for 20 minutes or until done. To cool, turn out onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet just after removing from oven (do not turn oven on until morning). In the morning, set oven to 350°. Bake rolls until brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix with hands until completely blended. Shape into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: nut custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 450 degrees, then lower temperature to 375 degrees and bake 20 more minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine crushed Oreos and margarine and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with oil.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Cream and combine the first 5 ingredients one at a time, stirring well between each.
In a second bowl, combine all other ingredients and add it gradually to the first bowl a bit at a time.
Place dough in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased and floured pan and bake in 350° oven for 50 plus minutes.

title: hot cheese
directions: Grind all ingredients through food grinder.
Add salad dressing to your taste.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms until browned in butter.
Combine all ingredients, except egg whites, in bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Place mushrooms, cap side down, on baking sheet.
Fill with mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° until puffy, approximately 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and place in a square baking dish.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all of the butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Chill for about an hour, then form into small balls and chill again, about 1 hour.
Then heat in a double boiler the paraffin and chocolate chips until melted.
Then dip the balls in the chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: coconut squares
directions: Stir flour and 1/4 cup sugar together, then cut in 1/2 cup butter with a pastry blender (or fork).
Press firmly into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with pineapple.
Combine 1 tablespoon soft butter, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Mix well and add the coconut.
Blend well and spread over the pineapple.
Return to oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Marinate meat in sauce overnight.
Yields enough marinade for 2 large London broils.

title: creamy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight before rolling into ball and coating with nuts.

title: my favorite brownies
directions: Combine oil, cocoa and sugar. Add vanilla and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° until top is dull and slightly firm.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400° Put muffins on baking sheet and toast for 5-10 min. Remove muffins from oven. Spread 1 tbsp. of pizza sauce on top of muffin. Take 1 tbsp. cheese and sprinkle on top of sauce.
Bake for about 8 min, until cheese is melted.

title: butterscotch slices(refrigerator cookie)
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and egg until creamy.
Add flour mixture, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Turn dough onto large piece of wax paper.
Shape into roll 2 inches in diameter.
Chill, slice and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: light old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Mix until all fruit and nuts are well coated with dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add brandy flavoring to mixture.
Mix with the fruit, nut, flour mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
About 1/2 hour before cake is done, brush top with honey.
Decorate with fruit and nuts.

title: broccoli chicken dish
directions: Brown chicken and sprinkle with paprika, garlic, oregano, Season-All and lemon juice.
Remove to baking dish when brown on both sides.
Cook broccoli according to package directions. Combine both soups and milk.
Mix the milk/soup combination well. Add milk/soup mixture and broccoli to chicken in baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: Place chocolate, milk and salt in top of double boiler. Cook until thickened, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and vanilla. Drop by tsp about 1 inch apart, onto well greased baking sheet. Bake 350° for 10 to 20 minutes, until edges around cookie are dry. Remove from pan right away.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Break into chunks.
Heat soup and mix in celery, mayonnaise, onion and chicken.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with 1/4 inch of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: In crock-pot, melt cheese on medium heat.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Add jalapeno pepper to taste.
(If you like it spicy, add some of the juice of the pepper also.)
Turn heat down.
Don't allow cheese mix to boil.
Heat on low for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve.

title: bread-and-butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, using a vegetable brush; drain on rack.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Add onions, garlic and salt.
Cover with ice; mix thoroughly.
Allow to stand for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly and remove garlic. Combine sugar, spices and vinegar; heat just to a boil.
Add cucumber and onion slices; heat for 5 minutes.
Pack loosely into clean, hot pint standard canning jars.
Process in boiling water bath canner for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions on package.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons Wesson oil for about 5 minutes (do not brown).
Add mushroom soup diluted with 1/2 can water, cooked rice and cheese.
Add broccoli and stir well.
Put in casserole and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
(Do not add salt and pepper, but you may add chopped mushrooms, if desired.)

title: potato or macaroni salad dressing
directions: Blend eggs.
Add sugar, mustard and butter and blend.
Then add vinegar and blend.
Boil in a double boiler or in a saucepan over low heat until slightly thickened.
Cool, then add 1 pint jar Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients into 2 logs.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip logs in chocolate and drain on rack.
Slice when cool and set.
Also, may make individual rolls.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk, soda and Karo to soft-ball stage. Add remaining ingredients. Beat until thick; drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, peppers, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper; mix up.
Fold in hash browns; turn into greased casserole.
Toss together corn flakes and 1 tablespoon of melted butter; sprinkle this over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until casserole is golden brown and potatoes are tender.
Serves about 6 or 8.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Makes 12 to 14 loaves.

title: barb's make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash and beat until smooth.
Will keep in the refrigerator 2 weeks.
Warm in the microwave or crock-pot.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown first four ingredients in Dutch oven. Drain fat.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and tomatoes. Bring to a boil.
Add salt, pepper and cabbage. Cook until cabbage is done.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugars, pecans and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Sprinkle chocolate chips in unbaked pie shell. Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Pie will become firm as it cools.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Whisk together all dressing ingredients in small bowl.

title: sesame sweet potato balls
directions: Be sure the sweet potatoes are mashed very smooth.
Beat in the sugar, ginger and egg yolks until fluffy.
Form tablespoons of the mixture into balls.
Mix the flour and water until smooth. Roll the balls in the mixture, then in the sesame seed.
Heat the oil to 375°.
Fry the balls in it until delicately browned. Drain and serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients well. Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Makes 1 quart.
Store in refrigerator.

title: original chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, mix together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually mix in flour mixture.
Mix well.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts with spoon. Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the chicken broth, celery soup and cream of chicken soup in.
Sprinkle on dried onions.
Add chicken pieces and cooked noodles.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: diabetic marinated cucumbers
directions: Blend water, sweetener, vinegar and seasoning.
Peel and thinly slice the cucumber.
Add liquid mixture.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: cobbler dump for camping
directions: In a Dutch oven, put peaches (with juice), pineapple (with juice), tapioca and mix well.
Sprinkle cake mixes on top.
Then sprinkle brown sugar on top and dot with margarine.

title: mexican meat pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Sprinkle with cornstarch; blend in enchilada sauce, parsley and drained mushrooms.
Set aside.
Put bottom crust in deep dish 9-inch pie plate.
Spread half of eggs in crust.
Spoon in meat mixture; top with cheese, then spread the rest of the eggs over cheese.
Put on top crust; seal and flute edge.
Cut slits in top for steam escape. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put on stove.
Let come to a close boil, then turn down to simmer for 30 minutes.
Take out cinnamon sticks and cloves before serving.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all except oil.
Shape by rounded tablespoons into balls in large skillet.
Cook in oil about 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate pound cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream the shortening and sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Melt white chocolate in double boiler or microwave.
(Microwave on High for 2 minutes and stir until thoroughly smooth.)
Cool and add to shortening-sugar mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake in a large tube pan (10-inch), greased and floured, in a preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Test for doneness by inserting a straw or toothpick.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add 4 tablespoons cold water, lemon juice, sugar and pineapple.
Mix and chill.
Mix 2 packages Dream Whip; combine with gelatin mixture.
Line a large bowl with wax paper.
Pinch angel food cake into small pieces. Alternate layers of cake and gelatin, ending with gelatin. Refrigerate overnight.
Turn onto plate.
Ice with Dream Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: baked elephant
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
Add brown gravy and cook 16 hours at 465°.
This will serve 3,864 people.
If unexpected guests arrive, the 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: taco dip
directions: Place chopped avocado, cream cheese, sour cream and lemon juice in blender.
Process until mixture is smooth.
Place on serving tray.
Sprinkle on taco mix.
Add lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and onions.
Place taco chips around edge and serve.

title: baked cheese sandwiches
directions: Make sandwiches and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard, onion (optional) and Worcestershire sauce. Pour mixture over sandwiches. Let stand for at least an hour or overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cut and serve with mushroom sauce made with 1 can mushroom soup diluted with 1/2 cup milk.

title: island style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving syrup.
In skillet, brown chicken in a little shortening; pour off fat.
Add reserved pineapple syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and garlic. Cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Add pepper and pineapple chunks.
Cook an additional 5 minutes or until done, stir occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and water and stir into sauce. Heat until slightly thickened.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: b.p.o.e. #38 "italian chicken"
directions: Skin chicken; place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with 1/2-inch of oil.
Lay several cloves of garlic in pan.
Season chicken. Cover tightly with foil.
Place in oven (350°) until done.
When removed from oven, leave foil for approximately 1/2 hour. Serve.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Place uncooked noodles in bottom of baking pan or dish.
Place raw chicken pieces on top of noodles.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soups and milk together; pour over chicken and noodles.
Cover.
Bake in 350°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.
In the last 10 minutes of baking time, remove the cover.

title: easy-cheesy lemon bars
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg; mix well.
Spread over bottom of pan.
Blend frosting with cream cheese and 2 eggs until creamy.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: butter balls
directions: Very finely chop nuts.
Mix together all other ingredients, then add the nuts.
Taking a rounded teaspoonful, roll into a ball and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cookies will crack slightly, but will be okay once cooled. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: kelly's hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Spread them on slices of bread.
Lay spread side up on cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, 1/2 stick melted margarine, vanilla and salt well and top with the following:
1/2 stick melted margarine, brown sugar, self-rising flour and pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.
For each cookie, drop 1/4 cup dough to form stem.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until cookies are firm and lightly brown.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool on racks.
Decorate using icing or peanut butter to affix assorted candies, raisins or nuts.
Yields 19 to 20 cookies.

title: crab and shrimp stuffed mushrooms
directions: Blanch mushroom caps in a little water for 10 minutes.
Saute garlic, onion, shrimp, crabmeat and parsley in butter.
Add milk and the eggs; mix in all other ingredients, adding bread crumbs a little at a time.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chicken in bacon and jalapeno wrap
directions: Salt
and pepper
chicken
breast.
Wrap
bacon
around sides and stick toothpicks
in to hold bacon.
Place jalapenos on top of chicken and
place	one
teaspoon
butter
on top of chicken. Wrap in foil and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook ground beef and onions in large skillet until beef is browned and onions are tender.
Stir in mushrooms, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons baking mix; mix well and set aside.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Place into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until well set.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl and beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: green peas delicious
directions: Saute butter, celery, onion and green pepper in pan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bologna salad sandwich filling
directions: Combine bologna, celery, onion and salad dressing or mayonnaise and mix well.
Makes about 6 sandwiches.

title: mondos white chili
directions: Boil chicken in pot for 15 minutes. Remove and shred. While chicken is boiling, chop up onions. Put in pan with butter and garlic powder. Saut onions until clear. Add 4 ounces chilies to onions and transfer to large pot. Add Great Northern beans, chicken broth, all the spices and the cooked shredded chicken. Simmer for 15 minutes. Enjoy.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Squeeze rinsed sauerkraut until dry.
Place in food processor until finely chopped.
In large bowl at high speed, beat margarine until fluffy. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each; beat in vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together alternating starting with dry.
Add dry mixture and water, ending with dry.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Pour butter in pan.
Bake 35 minutes until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
